  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_40">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_40</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A takisto by ma zauj脙颅malo, 脜戮e kto by mal s t脙陆mi v脜隆etk脙陆mi nak脙潞pen脙陆mi zbra脜聢ami 脙颅s脜楼 bojova脜楼, preto脜戮e pre Eur脙鲁panov to bude znamena脜楼 len 脛聫al脜隆iu militariz脙隆ciu, 脛聫al脜隆ie zadl脜戮ovanie, 脛聫al脜隆iu konsolid脙隆ciu a 脛聫al脜隆ie zdra脜戮ovanie. Mrz脙颅 ma, 脜戮e jedin脙陆, kto sa na samite postavil proti tomuto vojnov脙漏mu pl脙隆nu Leyenovej, bol op脙陇脜楼 iba ma脛聫arsk脙陆 premi脙漏r Viktor Orb脙隆n, 脜戮e v脜隆etci ostatn脙颅 芒聙聯 Macron, Scholz, Fiala, Fico a 脛聫al脜隆脙颅 芒聙聯 hlasovali za Leyenovej nav脙陆脜隆enie eur脙鲁pskej vojenskej a finan脛聧nej pomoci pre Zelensk脙漏ho namiesto toho, aby sa pridali k tomu Trumpovmu pl脙隆nu a zatla脛聧ili na Zelensk脙漏ho a dotla脛聧ili ho k mierov脙陆m rokovaniam. Zradili a sklamali t脙陆mto mnoh脙陆ch voli脛聧ov.
Ja viem garantova脜楼, 脜戮e my v hlasovan脙颅 Leyenovej vojensk脙陆 pl脙隆n nepodpor脙颅me a na脜隆ich voli脛聧ov nezrad脙颅me.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:34:16</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_33"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_46">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_46</del:identifier>
    <del:text>No dia 13 de fevereiro, 脙潞ltimo dia desse plen脙隆rio, o secret脙隆rio da Defesa americano, Pete Hegseth, disse a seguinte frase: 脗芦Os Estados Unidos j脙隆 n脙拢o est脙拢o dispon脙颅veis para garantir a seguran脙搂a da Europa脗禄. Clarinho como 脙隆gua. Como disse a presidente da Comiss脙拢o h脙隆 pouco, o tempo da ilus脙拢o acabou.
E, por isso, fez bem o Conselho Europeu, o Conselho da passada quinta-feira, em flexibilizar as regras do Pacto de Estabilidade e Crescimento, em criar uma nova linha de financiamento e at脙漏 em alterar o mandato do Banco Europeu de Investimento para permitir cr脙漏ditos em projetos na 脙隆rea da defesa, o que, ali脙隆s, mostra bem a forma adormecida como esta institui脙搂脙拢o europeia estava a olhar para a ind脙潞stria da defesa.
Portanto, o Conselho fez bem. Fez bem, mas n脙拢o chega. Porque 脙漏 urgente definir uma arquitetura de defesa europeia, porque, sem isso, o plano industrial que 脙漏 longamente falado continuar脙隆 vago, as compras conjuntas continuar脙拢o descoordenadas e a defesa da Europa continuar脙隆 dependente de outros, inclusivamente na sua componente nuclear.
Portanto, o fim do tempo da ilus脙拢o exige estas respostas r脙隆pidas e decididas, mas j脙隆 sabemos que a velocidade tem riscos 芒聙聰 e vale a pena, hoje, falar aqui destes riscos.脗聽O risco de, sistematicamente, se ultrapassar e passar ao lado do Parlamento Europeu; o risco de a Comiss脙拢o e a sua presidente passarem a ser essencialmente uma figura decorativa face a iniciativas pol脙颅ticas de Macron, Starmer, Merz ou, quem sabe, outros; e o risco de destruir a NATO, para a qual ningu脙漏m tem hoje uma alternativa cred脙颅vel.
Portanto, 脙漏 esse,脗聽Senhores Deputados, o nosso desafio: salvar a Europa 芒聙聰 a come脙搂ar pela Ucr脙垄nia, que tanto merece a nossa ajuda 芒聙聰, sem destruir as suas institui脙搂脙碌es. E 脙漏 nossa responsabilidade estar 脙聽 altura deste desafio.
(O orador aceita responder a uma pergunta 脗芦cart脙拢o azul脗禄)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:43:11</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_39"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_534">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_534</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Druga faza, to脛聧nije druga faza primirja, nije zapo脛聧eta, ali nisu niti eskalirali sukobi, barem ne do onog intenziteta koji je bio prije 15. sije脛聧nja.
Me脛聭utim, 59 talaca jo脜隆 nije oslobo脛聭eno. Mo脜戮da ve脛聡ina njih, na脜戮alost, vi脜隆e nisu 脜戮ivi, ali je nu脜戮no da Hamas oslobodi sve taoce i to odmah kako bi mir imao 脜隆ansu na Bliskom istoku. Hamas je zapo脛聧eo ovo poglavlje sukoba na Bliskom istoku teroristi脛聧kim napadom 7. listopada 2023. godine i stoga Hamas mo脜戮e i mora to poglavlje odmah zatvoriti osloba脛聭anjem talaca.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:53:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_289"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_247">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_247</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Hablemos claro: usted est脙隆 hablando de retornos, pero es un eufemismo, porque lo que estamos haciendo es dar v脙颅a libre a las expulsiones forzadas. Hoy se est脙隆 dando un paso m脙隆s debilitando las obligaciones internacionales que la Uni脙鲁n Europea tiene para garantizar los derechos humanos.
Son varias las razones por las que esta propuesta es inaceptable. En primer lugar, porque es anacr脙鲁nica y no tiene en cuenta las aportaciones positivas de las personas migrantes ni tampoco el mill脙鲁n de personas al a脙卤o que, seg脙潞n la propia Comisi脙鲁n ha dictaminado, necesitamos para mantener nuestro Estado de bienestar. 脗驴Por qu脙漏 van ustedes en contra de los intereses de la Uni脙鲁n Europea?
En segundo lugar, porque es inoperativa, pues est脙隆n demostrados la ineficiencia y el coste desproporcionado de las expulsiones脗聽frente a opciones de regularizar y dar derechos. Y, en tercer lugar, es cruel, porque externaliza las violaciones de derechos humanos generando Guant脙隆namos en pa脙颅ses fuera de la Uni脙鲁n Europea...</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:09:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_182"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_159">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_159</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:58:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_20"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_384">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_384</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Georgiana Teodorescu</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_435">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_435</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ich finde es deswegen gut, dass der Vorschlag der Europ脙陇ischen Kommission zum Clean Industrial Deal das gro脙聼e Ganze im Blick beh脙陇lt und 脙录ber die Sektoren hinweg tats脙陇chlich auch an Schwachstellen des Green Deals ansetzt. Wir haben zum Beispiel bisher ein absolutes Nachfrageproblem. Deswegen ist es richtig, Leitm脙陇rkte zu schaffen, deswegen ist es wichtig, zum Beispiel die Kreislaufwirtschaft anzukurbeln.
Aber man muss auch sagen, am Ende des Tages sind dort viele leere Versprechungen in Ihrem Vorschlag, insbesondere bei der fundamentalen Frage, wo eigentlich das Geld herkommen soll. Ohne die Investitionssicherheit werden wir es nicht schaffen, den Wandel hinzubekommen, deswegen vielen Dank f脙录r den Vorschlag, aber es liegt noch viel gemeinsame Arbeit vor uns.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:29:38</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_153"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_366">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_366</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Evin Incir,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_333">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_333</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The war in Ukraine has highlighted the consequences of inaction and overreliance on external partners for European defence. Beyond Ukraine, Europe has increasingly become the target of hybrid attacks and disinformation campaigns, directly threatening our political and economic stability.
But, despite all possible efforts, NATO remains the cornerstone of our security. If Europe needs to step up, any European-led initiatives must complement, not duplicate, NATO's role.
In its current form, the joint resolution is concerning. Instead of strengthening Europe's security, it promotes an alternative to NATO, undermines the autonomy of Member States in defence matters and risks deepening confrontation with the United States 芒聙聯 our most important ally.
Instead, Europe must focus on real security: replenishing stockpiles, strengthening transatlantic ties and investing in credible deterrence.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:21:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_58"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_225">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_225</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Rasa Juknevi脛聧ien脛聴,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_143">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_143</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:38:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_500">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_500</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Those working for peaceful transition are asking us, the EU, for support, not to steer the wheel, but to be the wind in their backs; to support decisively, but not naively 芒聙聯 decisively, because hesitation means losing this window of opportunity. We must ease sectoral sanctions that are crushing ordinary citizens. We need to support reconstruction, back democratic reforms and transitional justice, and ensure that the Syrian diaspora can contribute.
If we don't, others will fill the void, dear colleagues. But we must not support naively, because support must come with conditions: no new dictatorship, no new violence, no carving up the country like warlords, no exclusion of women opposition voices.
And to the foreign powers still meddling in Syria 芒聙聯 Turkey, Israel, Iran, Russia 芒聙聯 this is not your chessboard. Let Syrians finally reclaim their own future.
None of this is easy. None of this is quick. Fighting erupted again over the weekend, fuelled yet again by external interference and foreign fighters. This is exactly the vicious circle that Syrians want to break and that this new government must break. That's why we need to step up our support 芒聙聯 so that Syrians can rebuild their homes, heal their wounds and turn their country into a country for everyone.
(The President cut off the speaker)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:00:23</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_352"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_353">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_353</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wir werden unsere Union verteidigen, koste es, was es wolle. Wir werden an unseren K脙录sten k脙陇mpfen, wir werden an unseren Grenzen k脙陇mpfen. Wir werden auf unseren Feldern und Stra脙聼en k脙陇mpfen, und wenn es sein muss, auf jedem H脙录gel und in jedem Tal Europas. Denn Europa ist unsere Heimat, und f脙录r unsere Heimat werden wir uns wehren. Wir wollen keinen Krieg, aber wenn es sein muss, dann werden wir f脙录r unsere Freiheit k脙陇mpfen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:47:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_81"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_445">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_445</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Az infrastruktur脙隆lis fejleszt脙漏sek hi脙隆nya m脙隆shol is 脙漏rezteti a hat脙隆s脙隆t. P脙漏ld脙隆ul 2029 el脜聭tt nem v脙隆rhat脙鲁ak 脙潞j sz脙漏ler脜聭m脜卤- kapacit脙隆sok, a h脙隆l脙鲁zati csatlakoz脙隆sok sz脜卤k脙露ss脙漏ge miatt. A magyar ipar kiszolg脙隆ltatotts脙隆g脙隆t tov脙隆bb脙隆 n脙露veli az is, hogy b脙隆r a korm脙隆ny elhanyagolta az energiaberuh脙隆z脙隆sokat, most ad脙鲁fizet脜聭i p脙漏nzb脜聭l cs脙隆b脙颅tja be a gig脙隆szi energia脙漏hs脙漏g脜卤 k脙颅nai akkumul脙隆torgy脙隆rakat 脙漏s aut脙鲁gy脙隆rakat. 脙聧gy pedig tov脙隆bb emelkednek az 脙隆ram脙隆rak, amelyek k脙露zvetlen脙录l a magyar v脙隆llalkoz脙隆sok versenyk脙漏pess脙漏g脙漏t is vesz脙漏lyeztetik.
A magyar helyzet megmutatja, milyen k脙隆rokat tud okozni a megfizethet脜聭 energiak脙颅n脙隆lat hi脙隆nya a versenyk脙漏pess脙漏gnek. Ezzel szemben a tiszta ipari meg脙隆llapod脙隆sban kijel脙露lt strat脙漏gia kiv脙隆l脙鲁 alapot ad a fenntarthat脙鲁 eur脙鲁pai iparfejleszt脙漏snek.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:40:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_316"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_296">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_296</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Primera puntualizaci脙鲁n: para que los retornos sean posibles lo que hace falta es una arquitectura de acuerdos con los pa脙颅ses de origen y tr脙隆nsito que los permitan dignamente, una arquitectura diplom脙隆tica que actualmente no existe. Pero, en segundo lugar, centros de detenci脙鲁n en pa脙颅ses terceros, que no son de origen ni de tr脙隆nsito, por hasta dos a脙卤os, no solamente no son una soluci脙鲁n imaginativa, sino que caminan en contra del est脙隆ndar de derechos humanos al que se debe la Uni脙鲁n Europea. Y una 脙潞ltima puntualizaci脙鲁n: no tiene ning脙潞n sentido modificar el r脙漏gimen de tercer pa脙颅s seguro que negociamos y establecimos en el Reglamento sobre el Procedimiento Com脙潞n de Asilo de la UE antes de darle la oportunidad de entrar plenamente en vigor.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:17:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_219"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_443">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_443</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Die Frage, wie wir 脙录ber unsere Zukunft sprechen, die m脙录ssen wir sowieso f脙录hren. Wir k脙露nnen nicht nur jedes Mal Klimakrise sagen, wenn es um eine Flut geht, sondern wir m脙录ssen endlich langfristig denken: Das schulden wir den B脙录rgerinnen und B脙录rgern und vor allem den jungen Menschen in Europa.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:38:38</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_314"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_554">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_554</del:identifier>
    <del:text>What were Israel's options? Do nothing? Accept any demand made by the terrorists while the hostages were still being held? No country in the world would tolerate this! The EU did not negotiate with ISIS, nor did the US negotiate with Al-Qaeda!
Just as the EU sees peace negotiations between Russia and Ukraine as dangerous and invalid without security guarantees for Ukraine, it should analyse the situation between Israel and Gaza in the same manner, as long as the hostages are not released. If not, let us admit that we are applying double standards in EU institutions.
If we truly want peace, we should start by standing with those fighting against terrorism, not by legitimizing those who practice it - including here, in Europe, in Brussels, Strasbourg, Paris, and many other places.
Which of our children will be the terrorists芒聙聶 next victim?</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_384"/>
  </rdf:Description>
