  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_30">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_30</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Bogdan Rzo脜聞ca</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_130">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_130</del:identifier>
    <del:text>No se protege a la mujer gastando nuestro dinero en fomentar una ideolog脙颅a que nos denigra, confunde, victimiza y enfrenta, una ideolog脙颅a que nos est脙隆 destruyendo como sociedad. No se protege a la mujer callando ante los fundamentalismos que no respetan ni la vida ni la dignidad de las mujeres. No se protege a las mujeres cuando se trata de cambiar los valores fundacionales de la Uni脙鲁n Europea por la ideolog脙颅a woke o el islamismo.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:22:27</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_94"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_514">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_514</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Have we learned our lessons from the other so-called 'Arab Spring', which was nothing but the change from winter to winter in many Arab countries? We don't yet know. The outrage and violence last weekend show a different picture. We should align with international organisations, Commissioner. We should align with organisations important for us in Europe, especially in the field of border management, such as the UNODC.
We should also align with our strong partner in the region, Israel, which has taken care to ensure that the military threat from whatever regime will not increase but decrease, and which takes care of stability in the region, in the buffer zone there.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:19:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_212"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_330">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_330</del:identifier>
    <del:text>If we are weak, we are a target. If we are strong, we are safe. This is the principle that needs to guide us. This is why I say invest more in defence, to keep our citizens safe and invest more in common European projects in defence.
Commissioner Kubilius, we very much welcome the work that you're doing, and we're very much looking forward to the white paper that you're going to propose. Our expectation is to see projects in there which we at European level can do better that than Member States can do alone. And then we should also find the funds, the resources, to support the projects which the European Commission puts forward. We should show to the people of Europe that spending money at European level on defence is worth it, and that it is better spent than at national level.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:17:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_25"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_207">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_207</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Co z tego, 脜录e wynaleziono lek, 脜录e by脛聡 mo脜录e mamy nawet na niego fundusze, je脜聸li nie jest fizycznie dost脛聶pny w Europie, bo trafia na inne rynki, jest przedmiotem prac, presji w polityce mi脛聶dzynarodowej lub dostawy zostaj脛聟 odci脛聶te z powodu pandemii, napi脛聶脛聡 geopolitycznych, sankcji czy otwartych konflikt脙鲁w.
Europa dzi脜聸 sprowadza 80% lek脙鲁w lub substancji do ich produkcji. W niekt脙鲁rych przypadkach w og脙鲁le ich nie produkuje i w stu procentach zale脜录y od importu. Co je脜聸li, tak jak z energi脛聟 z Rosji, przyjdzie nam zmierzy脛聡 si脛聶 z dnia na dzie脜聞 z odci脛聶ciem importu tych lek脙鲁w. Potrzebujemy zatem ambitnego Critical Medicines Act, kt脙鲁ry jak najszerzej b脛聶dzie korzysta脛聡 z propozycji Sojuszu na Lek脙鲁w Krytycznych.
Istnieje pewien poziom produkcji lek脙鲁w, od kt脙鲁rego zale脜录y zdrowie i 脜录ycie Europejczyk脙鲁w, kt脙鲁ry wyznacza granice pomi脛聶dzy prostym biznesem a bezpiecze脜聞stwem. Potrzebujemy funduszu lek脙鲁w krytycznych, kt脙鲁ry pozwoli zabezpieczy脛聡 ten poziom w Unii, zasilanego na przyk脜聜ad z uelastycznienia niewykorzystanych 脜聸rodk脙鲁w z polityki sp脙鲁jno脜聸ci lub z procentowego udzia脜聜u w zliberalizowanej krajowej pomocy publicznej pa脜聞stw Unii, o co apelowa脜聜 w swoim sprawozdaniu Enrico Letta. Taki fundusz wzmacnia脜聜by europejsk脛聟 autonomi脛聶 i odporno脜聸脛聡 na przysz脜聜e kryzysy, wojny handlowe i r脙鲁wnowa脜录y脜聜 zaburzenie jednolitego rynku. W pe脜聜ni popieram ide脛聶 aktu o lekach krytycznych.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:03:01</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_152"/>
  </rdf:Description>
