  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_307">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_307</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:27:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_394">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_394</del:identifier>
    <del:text>For too long, Ireland has overlooked security and defence. While we remain committed to military neutrality, it does not equate to vulnerability. Securing our territorial waters and airspace is crucial, and the Government is prioritising the much-needed investment in our defence forces.
That is why I support Ireland's increased ambition in terms of urgent investment in primary radar, naval expansion and air defence. These are not luxuries: they are fundamental to our national security.
At the same time, Ireland's commitment to neutrality remains steadfast. But neutrality must be fit for purpose for the 21st century. That means contributing meaningfully to European security and contributing in areas in which we have a considerable degree of experience and expertise 芒聙聯 like peacekeeping, for example.
It's time to get off the fence and get on with defence.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:38:19</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_282"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_223">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_223</del:identifier>
    <del:name>脨聲脨录脨赂脨禄 脨聽脨掳脨麓脨碌脨虏</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_13">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_13</del:identifier>
    <del:text>La premi脙篓re, c芒聙聶est que nous devons savoir nous d脙漏fendre tout seuls. Alors, Madame la Pr脙漏sidente, achetons europ脙漏en, investissons europ脙漏en et produisons europ脙漏en. Oui, cent fois oui, 脙聽 ces 800脗聽milliards d芒聙聶euros, 脙聽 sortir la d脙漏fense de nos r脙篓gles budg脙漏taires et m脙陋me 脙聽 un emprunt commun. Oui 脙聽 une pr脙漏f脙漏rence europ脙漏enne, faute de quoi notre argent ira encore alimenter d芒聙聶autres 脙漏conomies que la n脙麓tre. Sans pr脙漏f脙漏rence europ脙漏enne, pas d芒聙聶autonomie strat脙漏gique et donc pas de souverainet脙漏.
Toutefois, il faut aussi dire les choses: on aura besoin de plus. Il faudra donc travailler tr脙篓s vite, Madame la Pr脙漏sidente, aux obligations europ脙漏ennes propos脙漏s par le Parlement et par un certain nombre de gouvernements en Europe. Il faudra aussi travailler aux modalit脙漏s de mobilisation de l芒聙聶脙漏pargne des Europ脙漏ens. L芒聙聶enjeu strat脙漏gique, 脙漏videmment, c芒聙聶est l芒聙聶argent, mais pas uniquement. La coordination sera cl脙漏. Il faut que nos arm脙漏es et notre million de soldats europ脙漏ens soient capables de travailler ensemble. Il faut aussi que nous avancions sur le b脙漏n脙漏fice europ脙漏en de la dissuasion nucl脙漏aire, sans bien s脙禄r remettre en cause la d脙漏cision souveraine nationale de l芒聙聶activer. C芒聙聶est 脙聽 ces seules conditions que nous pr脙漏serverons la paix pour nos concitoyens.
Il est 脙漏galement urgent, pour assurer notre s脙漏curit脙漏, de continuer 脙聽 soutenir l芒聙聶Ukraine, parce que la s脙漏curit脙漏 des Ukrainiens, c芒聙聶est aussi notre s脙漏curit脙漏. La d脙漏cision de Donald脗聽Trump d芒聙聶arr脙陋ter les livraisons d芒聙聶armements et le partage de renseignements ne nous rappelle qu芒聙聶une chose: nous devons reprendre notre destin en main, continuer 脙聽 essayer de convaincre l芒聙聶administration am脙漏ricaine qu芒聙聶elle fait une erreur, 脙漏videmment, mais, pendant ce temps, acc脙漏l脙漏rer notre aide 脙聽 l芒聙聶Ukraine et 脙陋tre force de proposition pour offrir des garanties de s脙漏curit脙漏 脙聽 l芒聙聶Ukraine 芒聙聯脗聽et 脙聽 nous-m脙陋mes. Cela passe notamment par l芒聙聶envoi de troupes europ脙漏ennes pour le maintien de la paix, une fois un accord obtenu. Nous devons dissuader une fois pour toutes la menace russe.
La deuxi脙篓me cons脙漏quence 脙聽 tirer, c芒聙聶est que notre mod脙篓le d脙漏mocratique est attaqu脙漏: 脙聽 l芒聙聶est par les ing脙漏rences russes et 脙聽 l芒聙聶ouest par le camp Trump et les alli脙漏s de cette internationale r脙漏actionnaire, ici m脙陋me dans cet h脙漏micycle. Monsieur脗聽Procaccini, quand vous pr脙漏tendez que les 脙聣tats-Unis ont donn脙漏 davantage d芒聙聶argent et de soutien 脙聽 l芒聙聶Ukraine que l芒聙聶Europe, c芒聙聶est faux. Vous le savez parfaitement et vous reprenez en ce sens 脙聽 la fois la propagande de Trump et la propagande du Kremlin. Nous sommes aux c脙麓t脙漏s de l芒聙聶Ukraine, nous avons 脙漏t脙漏 aux c脙麓t脙漏s de l芒聙聶Ukraine depuis le d脙漏but et nous continuerons de l芒聙聶脙陋tre jusqu芒聙聶脙聽 l芒聙聶obtention de la paix 芒聙聯脗聽la paix n芒聙聶脙漏tant en aucun cas la capitulation.
Madame la Pr脙漏sidente, le bouclier d脙漏mocratique doit 脙陋tre une cl脙漏 de vo脙禄te de ce mandat, et nous attendons votre proposition avec impatience autant qu芒聙聶exigence; mais commen脙搂ons d脙漏j脙聽 par appliquer les lois qui existent d脙漏j脙聽. O脙鹿 en est l芒聙聶enqu脙陋te sur le DSA? Le principe fondamental du droit, c芒聙聶est que, quand on viole les r脙篓gles, il y a sanction, et c芒聙聶est votre responsabilit脙漏 d芒聙聶en assurer le respect.
Chers coll脙篓gues, l芒聙聶Europe est une puissance stabilisatrice. Notre objectif, c芒聙聶est la paix, l芒聙聶ordre international et la promotion de la d脙漏mocratie. Nous avons les atouts pour 脙陋tre une puissance politique et militaire. Il est temps de s芒聙聶assumer comme telle.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:48:19</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_10"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_335">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_335</del:identifier>
    <del:text>This is not a theoretical discussion about where Europe shall head. This is a very serious discussion about how we can protect the international rules-based order, the national sovereignty of countries, and the right of countries to determine their own fate. Russia and Putin do not believe in that. They want their empire, they want their sphere of influence, and they are building a war economy that is threatening Europe, but also countries outside of the EU.
By this paper 芒聙聯 and I urge you, Commissioner, to be very strong and ambitious 芒聙聯 we show that Europe is united, that we can invest in defence, we can create military capabilities where Europe is united and can also act alone without the support of the United States. And that is something that negates the threat of Russia and protects democracy and peace in Europe 芒聙聯 that is what we must achieve.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:23:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_241"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_97">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_97</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The spirit of the consensus from the European Council 芒聙聯 unprecedented and unthinkable just a few weeks ago 芒聙聯 was felt, I would say, in most of the debate very strongly here as well, in this House of European democracy.
As many of you said, we have to think differently. Only in that way can we mobilise Europe's massive resources and start the deterrence build-up we need.
Many of you honourable Members were absolutely right to underscore that we cannot benefit from a peace dividend anymore. To the contrary, we must address the running security deficit. It's a huge task, and I would say that we must work on all levels 芒聙聯 European, national. We have to bring together our industry, our economic stakeholders.
As you heard from President von der Leyen, the first-ever Commissioner for Defence, Mr脗聽Kubilius, who also joined our debate this morning, together with the whole College of Commissioners, will be working day and night to achieve these goals.
We all realise that a powerful Europe means just and lasting peace in Ukraine, and a free and sovereign Ukraine means stronger Europe.
My colleague, Commissioner Kos, here with us today, has moved cooperation with Ukraine to a new level. She works tirelessly to support Ukraine in the path towards European membership. And I agree with her that we have to underline that we are living in historic times and therefore extraordinary challenges require extraordinary answers.
As we discussed the last time in this plenary, new geopolitics and transactional fragmentation of the world means that size matters again. Therefore, enlargement of the European family, enlargement of democracy and enlargement of respect for our values are the best answers for today's unstable world. The Commission will work hard to achieve these goals.
Let me conclude by the words of Mr脗聽Glucksmann, who said:
脗芦C芒聙聶est l芒聙聶heure de la v脙漏rit脙漏 pour l芒聙聶Europe脗禄 芒聙聯脗聽et je suis tout 脙聽 fait d芒聙聶accord avec lui.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:50:30</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_84"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_267">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_267</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Che cosa succeder脙聽 poi alle persone quando sono nel Paese terzo? Nessuno lo sa. Per di pi脙鹿, non vi sarebbe alcun obbligo di trasparenza di rendere pubblici questi accordi con i Paesi terzi. Perch脙漏?
Ancora: chi viene trovato sul suolo europeo senza documenti validi potr脙聽 essere detenuto fino a due anni 芒聙聯 prima erano 18 mesi. I dati, per inciso, ci dicono che pi脙鹿 si allunga il periodo di trattenimento, meno diventa probabile il rimpatrio. Ma questo 脙篓 un altro discorso.
Per le famiglie con i bambini minori non accompagnati, la detenzione sarebbe l'ultima opzione, ma non dovrebbe proprio essere un'opzione. Davvero l'Unione europea pensa di poter mettere in gabbia per due anni dei ragazzini che non hanno commesso alcun reato? Ci sono molte cose inaccettabili in questa proposta, sulle quali vigileremo e lavoreremo.
Caro Commissario, sentiamo dire spesso che l'approccio europeo deve essere fermo e giusto e finora abbiamo visto molto bene la parte ferma: per脙虏 vogliamo vedere anche la parte giusta.
(L'oratrice accetta di rispondere a una domanda "cartellino blu")</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:39:11</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_198"/>
  </rdf:Description>
