  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_262">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_262</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Em segundo lugar, a minha casa 脙漏 um lugar regido pela lei, e essa lei chama-se Acordos de Schengen. N脙拢o tem visto, n脙拢o entra. E quem entra sem visto, quem entra sem a minha vontade, tem de voltar para casa.
E este, Senhor Comiss脙隆rio, 脙漏 um primeiro passo. Tem falhas, com certeza, mas 脙漏 um primeiro passo positivo para o retorno daqueles que n脙拢o devem estar em nossa casa, porque a soberania nacional e a seguran脙搂a s脙拢o afetados por esta migra脙搂脙拢o ilegal.
O meu pa脙颅s era um pa脙颅s seguro at脙漏 h脙隆 dois anos e meio, agora n脙拢o 脙漏 um pa脙颅s seguro.
E o que 脙漏 que se passa em termos de direitos humanos? Os portugueses 芒聙聰 os europeus 芒聙聰 tamb脙漏m t脙陋m direitos humanos. S脙拢o eles o principal objeto dos direitos humanos. Porque 脙漏 que n脙鲁s ca脙搂amos os direitos humanos dos cidad脙拢os da Europa, dos cidad脙拢os dos nossos pa脙颅ses, dos cidad脙拢os de Portugal, para elevarmos os direitos humanos de outros que entram em nossa casa 脙聽 for脙搂a e sem convite?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:31:47</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_194"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_195">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_195</del:identifier>
    <del:text>N脙漏gy kulcspontot emeln脙漏k ki a n脜聭k helyzet脙漏r脜聭l:
1. B脙漏regyenl脜聭tlens脙漏g: Az EU-ban a nemek k脙露z脙露tti b脙漏rszakad脙漏k 脙隆tlagosan 13%, Magyarorsz脙隆gon 17%. Ez nemcsak a n脜聭ket 脙漏rinti h脙隆tr脙隆nyosan, hanem a f脙漏rfiakat is, mivel a csal脙隆d fenntart脙隆s脙隆nak terhe ar脙隆nytalanul r脙隆juk h脙隆rul.
2. Munkahelyi diszkrimin脙隆ci脙鲁: A n脜聭k gyakran alacsonyabb beoszt脙隆sban dolgoznak, mint az ugyanolyan v脙漏gzetts脙漏ggel rendelkez脜聭 f脙漏rfiak. M脙颅g egy f脙漏rfinek el脜聭ny, ha csal脙隆dos, addig a n脜聭k sz脙隆m脙隆ra sokszor h脙隆tr脙隆nyt jelent, ha gyermeket v脙隆llalna.
3. D脙露nt脙漏shozatalban val脙鲁 r脙漏szv脙漏tel: A politikai 脙漏s gazdas脙隆gi d脙露nt脙漏shozatalban a n脜聭k ar脙隆nya eleny脙漏sz脜聭. Eur脙鲁p脙隆ban a parlamenti k脙漏pvisel脜聭k 33%-a n脜聭, Magyarorsz脙隆gon csup脙隆n 15,7%-a!
4. A l脙隆thatatlan munka elismer脙漏se: A n脜聭k hozz脙隆j脙隆rul脙隆sa a t脙隆rsadalomhoz 芒聙聯 a gyermeknevel脙漏s, id脜聭sgondoz脙隆s, h脙隆ztart脙隆si munka 芒聙聯 az EU GDP-j脙漏nek 10%-脙隆t teszi ki.
Orb脙隆n Viktor korm脙隆ny脙隆ban kiz脙隆r脙鲁lag f脙漏rfi miniszterek d脙露ntenek. A TISZA P脙隆rt elengedhetetlennek tartja a n脜聭k bevon脙隆s脙隆t a d脙露nt脙漏shozatalba. A n脜聭k jogainak v脙漏delme 脙露sszt脙隆rsadalmi 脙漏rdek!脗聽Az脙漏rt dolgozunk, hogy legyen igazs脙隆gos b脙漏rez脙漏s, minden sz脙录l脜聭 sz脙隆m脙隆ra el脙漏rhet脜聭 脙漏s megb脙颅zhat脙鲁 b脙露lcs脜聭de 脙漏s 脙鲁voda, szabad orvosv脙隆laszt脙隆s, valamint hogy a csal脙隆dok ne anyagi gondok k脙露z脙露tt d脙露nts脙漏k el, mernek-e gyermeket v脙隆llalni.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_142"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_35">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_35</del:identifier>
    <del:name>脜陆eljana Zovko</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_216">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_216</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ehhez elengedhetetlen, hogy 脙露sszehangoljuk a szab脙隆lyoz脙隆st, 脙露szt脙露nz脜聭 k脙露rnyezetet teremts脙录nk az innov脙隆ci脙鲁nak, bele脙漏rtve az antibiotikum-kutat脙隆st. Meg kell 脜聭rizn脙录nk 脙漏s meg kell er脜聭s脙颅ten脙录nk az Eur脙鲁p脙隆n bel脙录li gy脙鲁gyszergy脙隆rt脙隆st, hogy cs脙露kkents脙录k a kiszolg脙隆ltatotts脙隆gunkat. A kritikus fontoss脙隆g脙潞 gy脙鲁gyszerek eset脙漏n egy k脙露z脙露s k脙漏szenl脙漏ti tartal脙漏kot kell l脙漏trehoznunk, amely biztos脙颅tja, hogy a tag脙隆llamokban ne forduljanak el脜聭 脙隆tmeneti gy脙鲁gyszerhi脙隆nyok. 脙聣s k脙录l脙露n脙露s figyelmet kell ford脙颅tanunk az 脙隆rva gy脙鲁gyszerekre 脙漏s a ritka betegs脙漏gek kezel脙漏s脙漏re. Ehhez 脙露sszehangolt fell脙漏p脙漏sre 脙漏s tag脙隆llamokon 脙隆tny脙潞l脙鲁 finansz脙颅roz脙隆si programokra van sz脙录ks脙漏g. A Critical Medicines Act garant脙隆lja ezeket, 脙漏s biztos脙颅tja, hogy Eur脙鲁p脙隆ban t脙露bb脙漏 ne forduljanak el脜聭 a pand脙漏mia alatt tapasztalt gy脙鲁gyszerhi脙隆nyok. Mert a nap v脙漏g脙漏n egyetlenegy dolog sz脙隆m脙颅t, hogy rendelkez脙漏sre 脙隆ll a gy脙鲁gyszer, amivel meg tudjuk menteni a beteg 脙漏let脙漏t, vagy nem.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:14:32</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_159"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_205">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_205</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:00:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_150"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_380">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_380</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A Uni脙拢o Europeia j脙隆 despende hoje tr脙陋s vezes e meia mais em gastos militares do que a R脙潞ssia e 1,3 vezes mais do que a China. Qual 脙漏 o sinal que se d脙隆 ao resto do mundo com esta corrida aos armamentos?
Como 脙漏 que desviar verbas dos fundos da coes脙拢o para os gastos militares pode corresponder 脙聽s necessidades e expectativas dos povos? O senhor deputado n脙拢o acha que se p脙碌e em risco n脙拢o apenas aquilo que era priorit脙隆rio para a vida dos povos, como, ainda por cima, se acentua a amea脙搂a e o risco de a confronta脙搂脙拢o e a guerra se tornarem mais globais?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:22:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_40"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_21">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_21</del:identifier>
    <del:text>However, you will not escape from the fundamental questions. You are talking about the security of Europe. Great. I would like to ask you how the security of Europe is served by cancelling elections in Romania and not allowing the candidate with 50脗聽% of support to run? How does allowing Tusk to destroy the opposition, take away all public money from the opposition party, and imprison MEPs serve Europe's security? How do your immigration policy and the Migration Pact serve European security? And the key question is: do you want Europe to defend itself from external threats, or for Europeans to kill each other? Instead of integrating Europe in the face of threats, as usual you choose your particular interests.
If the strength of Ukraine grew from the number of your empty words, the Ukrainian army now would be preparing to parade in Moscow. Do you want to help? You have EUR脗聽300脗聽billion of frozen Russian assets. Give them to Ukraine. That will be enough for five years of war. But you won't do it. You keep it because you want them to use to negotiate further resets with Russia. That is why you keep attacking America, provoking it to leave Europe. And you yourselves do not have those military capabilities. Your behaviour will cause the EU countries that border Russia to be in great danger.脗聽President Zelenskyy found about this after the summit in London. He will not provide the army weapons with your slogans, and that's why we need to change it.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:07:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_18"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_22">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_22</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Marc Botenga</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_The Left"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_281">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_281</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Onde n脙拢o existe a capacidade de retorno efetivo, vigorar脙隆 o condicionamento da entrada de migrantes. A melhor forma de favorecer uma pol脙颅tica migrat脙鲁ria positiva 脙漏, pois, com uma verdadeira estrat脙漏gia de retornos.
Precisamos de uma resposta que seja europeia, r脙隆pida, uniforme e clara em mat脙漏ria de retornos, que assegure o legado de Schengen, pelo que defendemos a implementa脙搂脙拢o de um regulamento, enquanto ato legislativo, para os retornos.
O regulamento a criar deve assentar em duas medidas essenciais: em primeiro lugar, o acompanhamento efetivo do migrante, desde a sua entrada at脙漏 脙聽 verifica脙搂脙拢o das condi脙搂脙碌es para a sua perman脙陋ncia. Por outro lado, devemos assegurar que esse processo de an脙隆lise seja breve, se cumpra dentro da jurisdi脙搂脙拢o da Uni脙拢o Europeia e obede脙搂a a regras que assegurem tratamento condigno dos migrantes, sempre no escrupuloso respeito dos seus direitos fundamentais.
Sejamos claros: precisamos de medidas que permitam os retornos, mas 脙漏 nosso dever fundamental garantir que estas medidas s脙拢o humanas e proporcionais.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:58:00</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_206"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_141">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_141</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Is that a made up concept or is it a reality that we actually are living day to day?
And then you also say that there is an ideology that is called gender equality. So you do not adhere to the fact that women are also humans and they have also human rights?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:36:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_104"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_98">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_98</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The Council is ready to do its job and follow up on the special European Council conclusions with the urgency that the moment requires, namely in the setting-up of the necessary instruments to bolster security in the European Union, and the ramping-up of the European defence, technological and industrial base.
Let me address the call of some MEPs on frozen assets. There will be a debate on it tomorrow. Last year, G7 leaders agreed to use the revenues from the immobilisation of Russian assets in the EU for repaying loans to Ukraine granted by the EU and G7 in the amount of USD脗聽50脗聽billion. The Council will consider all possible solutions in coordination with our international partners.
Thank you very much for this debate and thank you very much for your attention.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:53:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_2"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_536">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_536</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Los Acuerdos de Abraham de sus hermanos 脙隆rabes vecinos debieron avisarles. Pero como Gaza, y no solo Gaza, se acostumbr脙鲁 a vivir de dinero ajeno y Europa, los Estados Unidos y otros han pagado a los gazat脙颅es para ser refugiados eternos y odiar y querer asesinar jud脙颅os, han seguido abrazados al terrorismo, algo que se ha vuelto a ver en los canjes por rehenes: no parece que hayan aprendido.
Gaza tiene que ser limpiada de terroristas y se ha visto en estos meses que se est脙隆 a脙潞n lejos de ello. Convendr脙颅a a todos que la poblaci脙鲁n gazat脙颅 colaborara, que soltaran a todos los rehenes y se entregaran los t脙潞neles, todas las armas y esos uniformes planchaditos que se han utilizado en esos desfiles de propaganda cuando han soltado 芒聙聰humill脙隆ndolos芒聙聰 a los rehenes. Si no lo hacen, lo har脙隆n las fuerzas israel脙颅es.
Si los vecinos 脙隆rabes 芒聙聰Jordania y Egipto芒聙聰 acogieran a los gazat脙颅es, como los vecinos de Ucrania acogieron a los ucranianos, ser脙颅a m脙隆s f脙隆cil hacer todo este proceso, pero vamos a ver qu脙漏 disposici脙鲁n hay. En todo caso, la base terrorista no puede subsistir.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:55:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_373"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_312">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_312</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Imaginons un sc脙漏nario: apr脙篓s avoir conditionn脙漏 le maintien de la protection am脙漏ricaine 脙聽 l芒聙聶augmentation des budgets de d脙漏fense, Donald脗聽Trump annonce demain une condition suppl脙漏mentaire: le r脙漏armement de l芒聙聶Europe doit se faire aupr脙篓s de l芒聙聶industrie militaire am脙漏ricaine. Ce sera le moment de v脙漏rit脙漏 pour l芒聙聶Europe, le moment o脙鹿 elle sera confront脙漏e 脙聽 un choix existentiel: notre destin commun doit-il rester entre les mains du locataire de la Maison-Blanche, ou bien les nations europ脙漏ennes sont-elles capables de retrouver confiance en elles, de croire en leur g脙漏nie, d芒聙聶exploiter leur potentiel immense et de s芒聙聶affirmer sur la sc脙篓ne internationale comme une union d芒聙聶脙聣tats libres, capables de d脙漏cider et d芒聙聶agir selon ses propres int脙漏r脙陋ts?
Chers coll脙篓gues, disons-le tout haut: nous ne voulons ni d芒聙聶une Europe russe, ni d芒聙聶une Europe rendue barbare par l芒聙聶islamisme, mais pas non plus d芒聙聶une Europe am脙漏ricaine. Ce que nous devons rechercher et b脙垄tir, c芒聙聶est l芒聙聶Europe europ脙漏enne.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:46:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_227"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_289">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_289</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Dieser Vorschlag der Europ脙陇ischen Kommission, wenn er umgesetzt wird, wenn er den parlamentarischen Prozess hier im Haus gut 脙录bersteht oder vielleicht sogar noch besser wird, wird dazu f脙录hren, dass jene, die Asyl verdienen und brauchen, weil sie ein Recht dazu haben, das in der EU auch bekommen. Aber die gro脙聼e Mehrheit derer, die illegal kommen und gar kein Recht auf Asyl haben, die kann schneller und effektiver abgeschoben werden. Volle Unterst脙录tzung f脙录r die Kommission und f脙录r Kommissar Magnus Brunner auf diesem Weg!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:08:26</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_212"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_539">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_539</del:identifier>
    <del:text>En Palestina, una espiral de violencia ha terminado con el respeto a los derechos humanos y en el v脙鲁rtice de esa violencia est脙隆 la ocupaci脙鲁n ilegal de Palestina por parte de Israel, que tiene en vigor un sistema de脗聽apartheid pol脙颅tico que trata a los palestinos como infrahumanos sin derechos.
Denunciamos el genocidio de 60脗聽000 personas en Gaza y ahora debemos exponer las condiciones inhumanas de vida en la zona, los cortes de luz y agua y la ausencia de atenci脙鲁n sanitaria. Israel no atiende a razones porque no es un pa脙颅s democr脙隆tico, pero la Uni脙鲁n Europea debe exigirle que se permita la entrada del OOPS, de la ayuda humanitaria y de todo tipo de suministros y que cumpla con sus compromisos de alto el fuego.
Se脙卤ora comisaria, a estas alturas seguir manteniendo en vigor el Acuerdo de Asociaci脙鲁n con Israel no es negligencia, es colaboracionismo con cr脙颅menes de guerra. Est脙隆n hundiendo el prestigio reputacional internacional de la Uni脙鲁n Europea. No en nuestro nombre.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:00:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_376"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_473">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_473</del:identifier>
    <del:text>O Clean Industrial Deal n脙拢o 脙漏 apenas uma oportunidade, 脙漏 um compromisso com o crescimento e com a inova脙搂脙拢o, um compromisso de construir uma Europa que lidera na transi脙搂脙拢o energ脙漏tica, que gera riqueza e cria empregos de qualidade. Uma Europa que inspira e se destaca no contexto global.
A ind脙潞stria europeia foi sempre o motor do nosso progresso 芒聙聰 agora temos a responsabilidade de descarbonizar para crescer. Este 脙漏 o momento de agir, de avan脙搂ar mais r脙隆pido, com mais determina脙搂脙拢o, 脙漏 o momento de garantir que a aposta em tecnologias limpas impulsiona a economia, refor脙搂a a independ脙陋ncia energ脙漏tica e cria novas oportunidades de emprego.
A Europa do futuro come脙搂a hoje com inova脙搂脙拢o, com vis脙拢o, com ambi脙搂脙拢o, e come脙搂a connosco, com todos n脙鲁s.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:17:43</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_340"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_371">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_371</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Circa 650 de miliarde vor fi culese de la statele membre ale Uniunii, care vor fi nevoite s脛聝-脠聶i creasc脛聝 bugetele ap脛聝r脛聝rii 脠聶i s脛聝 se 脙庐mprumute. Alte 150 de miliarde vor fi acoperite din noi facilit脛聝脠聸i de 脙庐mprumut, cu dob脙垄nd脛聝. Majoritatea fabricilor de armament sunt acum 脙庐nchise 脙庐n 脠聸脛聝ri ca Rom脙垄nia pe motiv de decarbonizare a economiei. Ne vom 脙庐mprumuta pentru a importa armament. Rom脙垄nia are cea mai lung脛聝 grani脠聸脛聝 cu Ucraina, deci va avea 脠聶i cel mai mare cost militar relativ la PIB. Efectele? Supra脙庐ndatorare 脠聶i dezechilibru economic. A脠聶adar, cui profit脛聝 acest plan?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:09:11</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_267"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_168">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_168</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Questo atto non pu脙虏 essere giustificato: 脙篓 un episodio di violenza gravissimo, che trascende la satira e diventa un pericolosissimo strumento di incitamento all'odio verso le donne.
Si cerca di attaccare una donna che, invece di essere un bersaglio di violenza, dovrebbe essere vista come un esempio di come la forza, il merito e l'ambizione possano permettere a chiunque di raggiungere i propri sogni.
Giorgia Meloni rappresenta milioni di donne italiane che credono nel proprio potenziale, nella propria indipendenza, nel diritto di aspirare a grandi traguardi senza essere fermate dalla discriminazione e dai pregiudizi.
E tutto questo avviene nel silenzio pi脙鹿 assordante della sinistra e delle istituzioni. Sarebbe con questa violenza e intolleranza verso Giorgia Meloni che la sinistra intende difendere i diritti delle donne?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:08:03</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_120"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_226">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_226</del:identifier>
    <del:name>脦聯脦鹿脦卢脦陆脦陆脦路脧聜 脦聹脦卤脦陆脦鹿脦卢脧聞脦路脧聜,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_402">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_402</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I drugi element to kwestia preferencyjnych kredyt脙鲁w, kt脙鲁re przedsi脛聶biorcy musz脛聟 uzyska脛聡, ale bez tej buchalterii urz脛聶dniczej i biurokracji, kt脙鲁ra niesie za sob脛聟 脜聸rodki europejskie pochodz脛聟ce z bud脜录etu Unii Europejskiej. Je脜聸li b脛聶dziemy potrafili zaanga脜录owa脛聡 w to prywatny biznes, prywatnych przedsi脛聶biorc脙鲁w, pozosta脜聜e inne 脜聸rodki, jestem przekonany, 脜录e Europejska Unia Obronna b脛聶dzie dla nas wszystkich naprawd脛聶 wielkim sukcesem.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:49:12</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_288"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_366">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_366</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ci wszyscy, kt脙鲁rzy my脜聸l脛聟, 脜录e mo脜录emy sobie poradzi脛聡 bez NATO i ci wszyscy, kt脙鲁rzy pr脙鲁buj脛聟 w tej chwili obra脜录a脛聡 si脛聶 na Stany Zjednoczone, pope脜聜niaj脛聟 ogromny b脜聜脛聟d. Trzeba wyci脛聟ga脛聡 wnioski, trzeba i脜聸脛聡 do przodu. Polski prezydent Andrzej Duda zaproponowa脜聜 polskiemu rz脛聟dowi, a脜录eby zmieni脛聡 konstytucj脛聶 i wpisa脛聡 4% PKB z polskiego bud脜录etu jako gwarantowane 脜聸rodki na obron脛聶, mimo 脜录e Polska ju脜录 wydaje 5% PKB. Mam nadziej脛聶, 脜录e polski rz脛聟d przyjmie t脛聶 propozycj脛聶, 脜录e wi脛聶kszo脜聸脛聡 rz脛聟dowa przyjmie t脛聶 propozycj脛聶, i mam nadziej脛聶, 脜录e inne pa脜聞stwa cz脜聜onkowskie NATO zrozumiej脛聟, 脜录e trzeba wywi脛聟zywa脛聡 si脛聶 ze swoich zobowi脛聟za脜聞, 脜录eby Europa by脜聜a bezpieczna.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:01:44</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_264"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_432">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_432</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Maar terwijl we nog maar 脙漏脙漏n generatie de tijd hebben om onze planeet leefbaar te houden, komt de Europese Commissie met een agenda van greenwashing en clean washing. Mooie woorden lossen het klimaatprobleem niet op. Een blanco cheque aan vervuilende industrie stopt biodiversiteitsverlies niet en uitstel en versoepeling van milieuregels zijn geen antwoord op de voortgaande vervuiling van onze planeet.
Onder het motto van versimpeling wordt onze toekomst opgeofferd voor het blinde winstbejag van het bedrijfsleven. Hoe kortzichtig kunt u zijn, commissaris? Zelfs als u vindt dat geld het hoogste goed is, hoe gaat u dat dan verdienen op een uitgewoonde planeet?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:25:18</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_309"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_320">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_320</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Yvan Verougstraete</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Renew"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_316">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_316</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Disons les choses, cependant: nous d脙漏pensons d脙漏j脙聽 aujourd芒聙聶hui de deux 脙聽 trois脗聽fois plus que la Russie pour la guerre. Selon la presse allemande, nous avons actuellement quatre脗聽fois plus de navires de guerre que la Russie, trois脗聽fois plus de chars de combat et d芒聙聶artillerie et deux脗聽fois plus d芒聙聶avions de chasse, tandis que la Russie n芒聙聶arrive heureusement pas 脙聽 conqu脙漏rir m脙陋me un quart de l芒聙聶Ukraine. Avant que les Russes ne d脙漏boulent sur la Grand-Place de Bruxelles, il faudra du temps! Si vous ne voulez pas l芒聙聶entendre, ce n芒聙聶est pas grave. Ce sont les faits, mais vous pr脙漏f脙漏rez l芒聙聶id脙漏ologie.
Arr脙陋tez votre cin脙漏ma: tous ceux qui veulent plus d芒聙聶armes et plus de soldats, vous allez y envoyer vos enfants 脙聽 vous? C芒聙聶est ce que vous allez faire? Non, ce seront encore les enfants de la classe ouvri脙篓re qui devront mourir! Eh bien, nous ne l芒聙聶accepterons pas. Nous devons coordonner plus, pas d脙漏penser plus, et investir enfin dans la diplomatie.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:54:22</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_231"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_30">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_30</del:identifier>
    <del:text>So we need to step out, and we need to fill the gap left by Americans. And we need to do it now. It's not a matter of months or years, it's a matter of hours, days, maximum weeks. If we fail in Ukraine, if Ukraine falls, then we will not merely be back to square one, we will be in a much, much darker place, starting to rebuild Europe's security from shambles. We must not let this happen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:21:34</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_26"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_351">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_351</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The security of our citizens and the integrity of our borders depend on our ability to act swiftly and decisively. We must accelerate our efforts to enhance interoperability among Member States' armed forces. This is not just about spending more on defence; it's about ensuring that our forces can work seamlessly together.
We need also to integrate our defence industries and streamline our procurement processes to avoid duplication and inefficiencies. We also should move beyond intergovernmental agreements and build a genuine European Defence Union.
Our support for Ukraine is not just a moral imperative. It's a strategic necessity. We must provide more arms and ammunition, expand training operations and integrate Ukraine's defence industry into our own.
In doing this, we must remember that our ultimate goal is peace. We are strengthening our defence to avoid war, protect our values and ensure that the EU remains a beacon of stability in the world.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:44:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_253"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_189">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_189</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Ana Catarina Mendes</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_286">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_286</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Komise sice mluv脙颅 o mo脜戮nosti zp脜聶脙颅snit v脙颅zovou politiku nebo omezit obchodn脙颅 v脙陆hody, ale kde je povinnost tato opat脜聶en脙颅 skute脛聧n脛聸 ud脛聸lat? Kde je mechanismus, kter脙陆 by zajistil, 脜戮e neochotn脙漏 zem脛聸 okam脜戮it脛聸 poc脙颅t脙颅 d脜炉sledky sv脙漏ho jedn脙隆n脙颅? Nikde. Bez automatick脙陆ch nekompromisn脙颅ch opat脜聶en脙颅 tento n脙隆vrh op脛聸t skon脛聧脙颅 jako pouh脙陆 pap脙颅r bez re脙隆ln脙漏ho dopadu. Evropsk脙隆 komise m脛聸la jedine脛聧nou 脜隆anci p脜聶ij脙颅t s tvrd脙陆m, jasn脛聸 definovan脙陆m a vymahateln脙陆m syst脙漏mem sankc脙颅. M脙颅sto toho op脛聸t selhala. P脜聶edlo脜戮ila v脙隆gn脙颅 pl脙隆n, kter脙陆 se d脙隆 obej脙颅t, a my se pak budeme divit, 脜戮e n脙隆vraty st脙隆le nefunguj脙颅.
D脙隆my a p脙隆nov脙漏, pokud tento n脙隆vrh z脜炉stane v t脙漏to podob脛聸, nebude to 脜聶e脜隆en脙颅, ale bude to jenom dal脜隆脙颅 promarn脛聸n脙隆 p脜聶脙颅le脜戮itost.</del:text>
