  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_198">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_198</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Cecilia Strada</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_292">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_292</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wat Europa nodig heeft, is een massale terugkeerstrategie, verplichte terugname door de landen van herkomst, grootschalige uitzettingen en een einde aan het misbruik van de beroepsprocedures. Landen die hun illegalen niet terugnemen, moeten daar ook de gevolgen van dragen. Geen geld, geen visa, geen handel. Europa moet eindelijk durven kiezen voor een daadkrachtig remigratiebeleid dat onze grenzen, onze welvaart en onze veiligheid beschermt. Maar dat is helaas niet de bedoeling van de Europese Unie.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:12:15</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_215"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_490">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_490</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Reindustrializar Europa con un modelo sostenible y competitivo solo ser脙隆 posible si garantizamos energ脙颅a asequible para nuestras industrias y ciudadanos. Necesitamos m脙隆s renovables e interconexiones para una Uni脙鲁n de la Energ脙颅a real y mercados e instrumentos que reflejen esta asequibilidad para la industria.

Adem脙隆s, la financiaci脙鲁n es una condici脙鲁n imprescindible. Es una buena noticia que este plan venga acompa脙卤ado de recursos, pero debemos asegurarnos de que el pr脙鲁ximo Marco Financiero Plurianual contin脙潞e en esa direcci脙鲁n. Necesitamos apostar por campeones europeos capaces de competir a nivel global. Este pacto es tambi脙漏n una oportunidad para fomentar el sector de las tecnolog脙颅as limpias para modernizar nuestra base industrial y mejorar nuestras condiciones de vida.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_348"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_422">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_422</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Chers coll脙篓gues, ces derniers jours, nous voyons nos concitoyens et nos entreprises se mobiliser pour acheter davantage europ脙漏en, notamment pour nos technologies propres. C芒聙聶est une chance pour nos bases industrielles, et nous devons r脙漏pondre 脙聽 cette attente. Nous avons un march脙漏 de 450脗聽millions de consommateurs; c芒聙聶est un levier 脙漏conomique gigantesque. Ne soyons pas modestes.
Ce pacte introduit les premiers 脙漏l脙漏ments de pr脙漏f脙漏rence europ脙漏enne. C芒聙聶est un bon d脙漏but, mais il faut aller plus loin face 脙聽 un monde instable. Monsieur le Commissaire, je compte sur vous pour continuer en ce sens. L芒聙聶Europe doit choisir: d脙漏fendre son industrie ou s芒聙聶effacer.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:10:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_300"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_218">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_218</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Alice Teodorescu M脙楼we</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_322">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_322</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Accanto ad alcuni che abbiamo identificato come problemi, per脙虏, ce ne sono altri, di scenari: oltre a quello Russia-Ucraina, c'脙篓 il Medio Oriente, c'脙篓 il Centrafrica, ci sono altri soggetti pericolosi per noi, c'脙篓 la Cina, c'脙篓 il ruolo della Turchia, c'脙篓 il ruolo dell'Iran, c'脙篓 l'islamismo che avanza.
Ecco, nel libro bianco mi aspetto che ci siano valutazioni di questo tipo, perch脙漏 avremmo bisogno di un'industria della difesa, avremo bisogno di dual use, avremo bisogno di forze armate sempre pi脙鹿 preparate e di nostri soldati sempre pi脙鹿 sicuri, perch脙漏 a loro va il nostro grazie.
E, come ha detto nella relazione di Niinist脙露, c'脙篓 anche da guardare alla popolazione, che deve essere pi脙鹿 preparata. E soprattutto ai giovani dobbiamo parlare, affinch脙漏 possano avere pi脙鹿 amor di patria e capacit脙聽 di difesa.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:04:56</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_234"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_329">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_329</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Anna St脙录rgkh</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Renew"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_414">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_414</del:identifier>
    <del:text>My home country, Finland, shares the EU芒聙聶s longest border with Russia芒聙聰over 1,300 kilometres.
The Finnish Defence Forces have shown how decades of commitment is now bearing fruit.
Conscription, military training, and investments in defence have long been among the EU芒聙聶s best.
We are ready to defend our borders.
Meanwhile, some EU countries have neglected their duties, keeping defence spending minimal while expecting others to bear the burden.
Now the era of free riding is over 芒聙聰 we cannot start to fund countries that have failed to prepare.
Defence is not a charity - it芒聙聶s everyone芒聙聶s duty.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_132"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_499">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_499</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Les violences de ces derniers jours, qu芒聙聶exploitent sans honte les valets de Bachar脗聽el-Assad, y compris dans ce Parlement, alors qu芒聙聶ils ont couvert sans ciller un demi-million de morts, disent tout de l芒聙聶脙漏tat dans lequel cinquante脗聽ans de dictature ont laiss脙漏 la Syrie: d脙漏chir脙漏e par des tiraillements communautaires et en proie aux interventions 脙漏trang脙篓res les plus toxiques.
Que doit faire l芒聙聶Europe? Aider la population 脙漏puis脙漏e, qui sort d芒聙聶ann脙漏es de t脙漏n脙篓bres, s芒聙聶assurer que le pouvoir en place met ses actes en conformit脙漏 avec ses paroles, continuer de combattre Daech, qui reste une menace, et aider 脙聽 la stabilisation de la Syrie. Nous devrons 脙陋tre d芒聙聶autant plus engag脙漏s que les 脙聣tats-Unis risquent de se d脙漏tourner de l脙聽 comme d芒聙聶ailleurs. La stabilit脙漏 de la nouvelle Syrie est dans notre int脙漏r脙陋t et celui de la r脙漏gion.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:59:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_229"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_420">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_420</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Pokud chcete, pane komisa脜聶i, skute脛聧n脛聸 pomoci pr脜炉myslu a nav脙颅c pomoci ihned, tak p脜聶edlo脜戮te n脙隆vrh, kter脙陆 bez prodlen脙颅 v脙陆razn脛聸 zlevn脙颅 poplatky za emise sklen脙颅kov脙陆ch plyn脜炉, a nam脙颅sto nov脙漏ho klimatick脙漏ho c脙颅le pro rok 2040 zru脜隆te ten c脙颅l pro rok 2030.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:08:20</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_147"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_206">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_206</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Paulo Cunha</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_526">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_526</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The first priority for Gaza currently is to resume full access to humanitarian aid. Let us recall that there are 3.1脗聽million people who are affected by 15 months of conflict ahead of the January ceasefire. The local population should not again suffer from the hostilities from all sides.
The European Union and its Member States are among the biggest financial supporters of the Palestinians, and currently the largest donors to the Palestinian Authority and to UNRWA. It has already mobilised an additional amount of EUR脗聽120脗聽million for humanitarian assistance. Since the onset of the Gaza crisis, this brings our total contribution to EUR脗聽450脗聽million.
The脗聽package of essential services includes food, clean water, healthcare and shelter. So far, 4脗聽500 tonnes of humanitarian cargo have been transferred via humanitarian air bridge flights to Gaza. The European Union has also expanded its civil protection mechanism for medical evacuations in Gaza. A blockage of the delivery of humanitarian assistance and interruption of services such as electricity would have devastating consequences for the population on the ground.
Second, the extension of the ceasefire or a move to the second stage of the ceasefire and release of all hostages are the only ways to permanently end the hostilities, and it would allow us to start the early recovery and reconstruction of Gaza.
While European Union efforts are currently focusing on scaling up humanitarian support, we are also preparing for a long recovery and reconstruction phase. On 18脗聽February, the European Union released its Gaza Rapid Disaster Needs Assessment, together with the United Nations and the World Bank. This assessment looks at the damages, losses and needs. It estimates that EUR脗聽49脗聽billion are required over the next decade. The Egyptian-led reconstruction plan came to similar conclusions.
Housing requires the largest share of recovery needs 芒聙聯 about 30脗聽% 芒聙聯 followed by the health sector, commerce and industry, and agriculture and food. Given the magnitude of needs, the European Union cannot act alone. The international community must take collective and coordinated efforts to support Gaza's recovery and reconstruction. This is why we are working closely with our Arab partners. We welcome the Arab Recovery and Reconstruction Plan that was endorsed at the emergency summit of the League of Arab States in Cairo on 4脗聽March. We are studying the technical details of the plan in order to identify and create possible synergies, and we look forward to the upcoming international conference on Gaza that Egypt will host soon.
Large-scale recovery and reconstruction can only start when there is stability on the ground. This includes arrangements on the governance and security of Gaza. We firmly reject any attempt of relocation of the population or of territorial change in Gaza and the West Bank. Discussions on the recovery and reconstruction of Gaza must involve the Palestinians. The Palestinian Authority is their legitimate body.
When it comes to Gaza governance, we see the Palestinian Authority as the only viable partner. This is why we are committed to supporting a reformed Palestinian Authority and avoid its fiscal collapse. Last year, the Commission disbursed almost EUR脗聽400脗聽million in emergency funding to address the most urgent needs.
We are now preparing a multi-year, comprehensive programme for the Palestinian recovery and resilience. It is based on the reform agenda of the Palestinian Authority, and we are encouraging Israel to support it by releasing withheld tax revenues.脗聽We hope that other regional stakeholders, including in the Gulf, will also support this approach.
Finally, I want to highlight the essential role that UNRWA has played. It has delivered more than half of the entire emergency response in Gaza over the last 15 months. As a provider of many essential services to Palestinians, also beyond Gaza, UNRWA has an important role. They are a humanitarian and development actor. As European Commission, we will continue our support to the Palestinian refugees and to the UN agency.
Let me finish by saying that I am looking forward to high-level political dialogue with the Palestinian Authority in April. It will take place on 13 or 14脗聽April and will be a good occasion to take stock of the reform achievements.
We must not forget the central role of the Palestinian Authority and the role which it will have in the day after in Gaza. Thank you and I am looking forward to your debate.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:35:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_349"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_177">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_177</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Zum Prinzip脗聽1: Freiheit von genderbasierter Gewalt. Das Verbrechen der Vergewaltigung ist als EU-weiter Straftatbestand zu definieren; das muss sofort geschehen. Online芒聙聭Gewalt ist aktiv zu bek脙陇mpfen. Der DSA muss konsequent umgesetzt werden, und die Plattformen m脙录ssen in die Pflicht genommen werden, menschenverachtende Inhalte sofort zu l脙露schen. Und die laufenden Verfahren m脙录ssen auch z脙录gig abgeschlossen werden, auch wenn es sich um Riesenkonzerne handelt.
Zum Prinzip脗聽2: Zugang zu sexueller und reproduktiver Gesundheit. Das bedeutet auch das Recht auf sichere Abtreibung, auch das muss klar zum Ausdruck kommen.
Die Prinzipien脗聽3 bis 5: Gleichstellung am Arbeitsmarkt und Familienleben. Die Lohntransparenz芒聙聭Richtlinie muss in allen Mitgliedstaaten rasch umgesetzt werden, und Berufe, wo viele Frauen t脙陇tig sind, wo haupts脙陇chlich Arbeit am Menschen geleistet wird, geh脙露ren dringend aufgewertet. Wenn mehr Mittel f脙录r die Verteidigung umgeschichtet werden, dann darf das nicht auf Kosten der Frauen gehen.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:21:31</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_129"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_245">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_245</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Alberico Gambino</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_80">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_80</del:identifier>
    <del:text>It's clear what we Europeans have to do: the exact opposite to what Moscow, Beijing, but also Donald Trump, is dreaming about. We must get united and we must get much, much, much stronger.
From that point of view, the summit was a good start. But not everything is about money. We need a strong and clear foreign policy to be able to represent the interest of Europeans. Common purchases are good, but it's not the same as the European defence that we desperately need, and this is what Manfred Weber was talking about.
So for me, the summit was a good start. But we must go much, much further and we must go much, much quicker, because there is very little time left.
(The speaker agreed to take a blue-card question)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:29:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_69"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_485">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_485</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Reindustrializar Europa con un modelo sostenible y competitivo solo ser脙隆 posible si garantizamos energ脙颅a asequible para nuestras industrias y ciudadan脙颅a. Necesitamos m脙隆s renovables e interconexiones para una Uni脙鲁n de la Energ脙颅a real y mercados e instrumentos que reflejen esta asequibilidad para la industria.
Adem脙隆s, la financiaci脙鲁n es una condici脙鲁n imprescindible. Es una buena noticia que este plan venga acompa脙卤ado de recursos, pero debemos asegurarnos de que el pr脙鲁ximo Marco Financiero Plurianual contin脙潞e en esa direcci脙鲁n. Necesitamos apostar por campeones europeos capaces de competir a nivel global. Este pacto es tambi脙漏n una oportunidad para fomentar el sector de las tecnolog脙颅as limpias para modernizar nuestra base industrial y mejorar nuestras condiciones de vida.</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_345"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_100">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_100</del:identifier>
    <del:name>El脜录bieta Katarzyna 脜聛ukacijewska</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_135">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_135</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Marit Maij</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_535">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_535</del:identifier>
    <del:text>La Uni脙鲁n Europea debe impulsar las fases dos y tres del alto el fuego o solo quedar脙隆n dos escenarios posibles: una nueva guerra o el plan del resort de Trump.
Existe una estrategia silenciosa de ocupaci脙鲁n por parte de Israel que se ha apropiado el 16脗聽% de las tierras agr脙颅colas de Gaza, al igual que en Cisjordania y Jerusal脙漏n, donde la expansi脙鲁n de asentamientos ilegales israel脙颅es, la confiscaci脙鲁n de tierras y el desplazamiento forzoso se han intensificado. Los puestos fronterizos han aumentado un 228脗聽% y se est脙隆n eliminando barrios enteros. Los palestinos no tienen la culpa del terrorismo de Ham脙隆s,脗聽que hay que combatir con firmeza. La ocupaci脙鲁n se consolida en prime time.
Mientras tanto, el Gobierno de extrema derecha israel脙颅 proh脙颅be que el OOPS proporcione ayuda a m脙隆s de 500脗聽000脗聽refugiados y asfixia, con un 80脗聽% de impuestos sobre la financiaci脙鲁n extranjera, a las ONG que no comulgan con dicho Gobierno, silenciando a los ciudadanos israel脙颅es dem脙鲁cratas. Debemos seguir hablando de paz en Gaza, de los dos Estados y, sobre todo, del cumplimiento del Derecho internacional.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:54:09</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_372"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_332">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_332</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Micha脜聜 Kobosko</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Renew"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_156">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_156</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Aurelijus Veryga</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_3">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_3</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Ursula von der Leyen,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_22">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_22</del:identifier>
    <del:text>'If something is worth building, it is worth defending' 芒聙聯 these are the words is Se脙隆n Lemass, former Irish Taoiseach and leader who submitted Ireland's application to join the European Economic Community. My country is militarily neutral. We won't join a military alliance, but that doesn't mean we don't take sides. We are on the side of freedom, democracy, multilateralism, and a global order based on international law.
Ireland is lucky. We are an island in the Atlantic, surrounded by non-threatening nations. But I know my friends and colleagues along the eastern border of our Union live in fear of the return of Russian imperialism. I see the worry in their eyes. I hear the pain in my friends' voices when they speak about living under Russian occupation before independence. That is why I will not stand in the way in terms of defending your homelands and your homes.
And Europe must collectively defend itself. Our unity is our strength. This is a big change, and I know I will be castigated by the extremists at home, on the left and on the right, but it is morally the right thing to do. Ireland will not join NATO, but I firmly believe we must ensure our fellow Member States have the resources needed to defend their sovereignty and their values.
We must have defence bonds. We must make it easier for the states to strengthen their militaries by relaxing Stability and Growth Pact rules. We must all work together on sharing intelligence and ensuring interoperability and defence systems and energy security. Ireland must use every possibility under our constitution to support our European friends: humanitarian aid training, non-lethal weapons, support for demining initiatives, financial support and increasing our own military defence capabilities.
I will say it again, if it is worth building, it is worth defending. There has never been a greater force for peace, prosperity and progress than the European Union and we must defend this.
(The speaker agreed to take a blue-card question)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:09:34</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_19"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_250">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_250</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Und trotz der weitreichenden Auswirkungen auf Grundrechte hat die Kommission es erneut verpasst, die m脙露glichen Auswirkungen ihres Vorschlags zu analysieren脗聽芒聙聯 es gibt wieder keine Folgenabsch脙陇tzung. All das f脙录gt sich nahtlos in das Narrativ der Kommission unter Frau von der Leyen, Migranten seien potenziell eine Bedrohung. Diese Erz脙陇hlung lehne ich ab. Und Herr Brunner, wir werden einige Verbesserungen f脙录r Ihren Vorschlag einarbeiten m脙录ssen, damit das Ganze funktioniert.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:15:08</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_185"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_258">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_258</del:identifier>
    <del:text>U脜戮 neubehne pomaly t脙陆脜戮de脜聢, aby svetov脙漏 m脙漏di脙隆 nezaplavili inform脙隆cie o tom, ako nejak脙陆 sadistick脙陆 vrah no脜戮om n脙隆hodne bod脙隆 do 脛戮ud脙颅. Neubehne t脙陆脜戮de脜聢, aby sme sa nedopo脛聧uli o 脜戮en脙隆ch a de脜楼och, ktor脙漏 s脙潞 vra脜戮den脙漏 脛戮u脛聫mi, ktor脙颅 boli vyhosten脙颅, no v rozpore so z脙隆konom neopustili krajiny, kde u脜戮 d脙隆vno nemali 脛聧o robi脜楼.
Eur脙鲁pa bojuje s obrovsk脙陆m n脙隆rastom kriminality, bojuje s obrovsk脙陆m n脙隆rastom terorizmu a mus脙颅 sa t脙陆chto 脛戮ud脙颅 skr脙隆tka zbavi脜楼. Nemaj脙潞 tu 脛聧o robi脜楼 a treba ich vyhos脜楼ova脜楼 tak, ako ich v Amerike za脛聧al vyhlasova脜楼 Trump. A preto nech脙隆pem, ako m脙麓脜戮u niektor脙颅 脛戮avicov脙颅 progres脙颅vni poslanci z tohto pl脙漏na obhajova脜楼 pr脙颅tomnos脜楼 vrahov a n脙隆siln脙颅kov v Eur脙鲁pe a hovori脜楼, 脜戮e je to poru脜隆ovanie ich 脛戮udsk脙陆ch pr脙隆v, ke脛聫 ich odtia脛戮 dostaneme. Nemaj脙潞 tu 脛聧o robi脜楼 a zasl脙潞脜戮ia si okam脜戮ite vypadn脙潞脜楼.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:26:01</del:timestamp>
