  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_404">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_404</del:identifier>
    <del:text>In 1990, we regained our independence after 50 years of occupation by the Soviet Empire. My message on this day is very clear: we, Lithuanians, don't want to go through the same in the 21st century 芒聙聯 another occupation and another independence day. I don't want my sons and my grandkids to face it and I don't want your 芒聙聯 in the left, in the centre and the right 芒聙聯 kids and grandkids to face the fate of Ukrainian children. That is why I wish Lithuanians a Happy Independence Day from the 1990s.
And to all my friends in Europe, I want to say: independence is easy to lose, but very hard to regain. We must now be ready to defend our European independence. I would like to remind you that Russia, this year, in so-called purchasing power parity terms, will spend for the war more than all of us in the European Union are going to spend.
I would also like to remind you of the numbers which NATO Secretary-General Mark Rutte is always repeating. Now, at this moment, Russia during three months produces more weapons than all NATO Member States, including the United States, Canada, Great Britain, Norway and us in the European Union are producing during one year. We must really understand what this means. That is why I want to thank all of you for all of your support during this discussion, for Ukraine and for the defence of Europe.
Next week, we will present the white paper on the future of European defence, with a focus on investment capabilities and defence industry. We will continue our discussion and we will put words into action to deter aggression and prevent war.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:51:56</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_224"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_31">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_31</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Komisja Europejska wykorzystuje wojn脛聶 na Ukrainie i kryzys w relacjach z administracj脛聟 ameryka脜聞sk脛聟 jako pretekst do przyspieszenia budowy europejskiego superpa脜聞stwa. Prawdziw脛聟 intencj脛聟 Komisji Europejskiej nie jest udzielenie pomocy ogarni脛聶tej wojn脛聟 Ukrainie czy rozwi脛聟zanie jakiegokolwiek europejskiego problemu. Kolejne problemy to tylko pretekst do zaw脜聜aszczania kolejnych kompetencji przez Uni脛聶. Mieli脜聸my ju脜录 propozycje zmiany unijnych traktat脙鲁w, reform脛聶 procesu decyzyjnego, w tym likwidacj脛聶 prawa weta, i po ostatnim posiedzeniu Rady Europejskiej dostajemy decyzj脛聶 o kolejnym eurod脜聜ugu, aby nast脛聶pnie w脜聜a脜聸nie tymi 脜聸rodkami szanta脜录owa脛聡 finansowo pa脜聞stwa narodowe, jak w przypadku krajowych plan脙鲁w odbudowy. Nie ma naszej zgody na przekazywanie nowych kompetencji Unii.
Teraz Unia rzekomo chce si脛聶 zajmowa脛聡 rozwojem przemys脜聜u zbrojeniowego w Europie. Najlepsza pomoc, jakiej mo脜录e udzieli脛聡 Europie ta Komisja i ta Izba, to powstrzymanie si脛聶 od jakiegokolwiek dzia脜聜ania. Europy nie da si脛聶 obroni脛聡 ani rezolucjami, ani scentralizowan脛聟 w脜聜adz脛聟 biurokracji. Dzisiaj potrzeba nam jak nigdy dot脛聟d silnych pa脜聞stw narodowych. To one maj脛聟 dzia脜聜a脛聡, to one maj脛聟 rozwija脛聡 sw脙鲁j przemys脜聜 militarny i budowa脛聡 narodow脛聟 armi脛聶, samodzielnie decydowa脛聡, czego im potrzeba i w jakich ilo脜聸ciach, a nie anonimowy urz脛聶dnik z Brukseli.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:22:45</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_27"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_44">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_44</del:identifier>
    <del:text>But none of this would have been necessary if we had a Commission that was more preoccupied with creating growth instead of bureaucracy. If you had a Commission that was willing to prioritise within the EUR 1.2 trillion budget. Ursula von der Leyen, you are making the Europeans into welfare junkies and you're doing it from borrowed money.
So let me put this very simple. We want our money back!
N脙楼r vi ser p脙楼 det fra et dansk perspektiv, m脙楼 man sige, at EU har gjort meget lidt. Igen og igen har Danmark st脙赂ttet Ukraine milit脙娄rt og 脙赂konomisk, og igen og igen har vi set, hvordan de st脙赂rste EU medlemsstater; Tyskland, Frankrig, Italien og Spanien ikke har fulgt trop. S脙楼 det er let at give Trump skylden for den situation, Ukraine st脙楼r i. Men hvis man virkelig vil forst脙楼, hvorfor vi tre 脙楼r inde i krigen har et EU, der ikke er i stand til at forsvare sig selv, har et EU, der ikke er i stand til at forsvare Ukraine, s脙楼 skal vi se indad. Der har v脙娄ret alt for lidt handling og alt for meget snak, og det forts脙娄tter desv脙娄rre.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:40:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_37"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_454">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_454</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Votre pacte pour une industrie propre est une h脙漏r脙漏sie id脙漏ologique de plus. Par exemple, vous voulez passer 脙聽 32脗聽% d芒聙聶脙漏lectrification d芒聙聶ici 脙聽脗聽2030, mais vous fuyez la seule 脙漏nergie capable de nous faire atteindre cet objectif: le nucl脙漏aire, 脙聽 peine mentionn脙漏 dans votre pacte. Nos industriels n芒聙聶arrivent d脙漏j脙聽 plus 脙聽 脙陋tre comp脙漏titifs, mais vous continuez 脙聽 leur imposer des objectifs hors-sol, comme la neutralit脙漏 carbone en脗聽2050. En r脙漏alit脙漏, avec votre pacte, notre industrie ne sera ni propre ni sale: elle dispara脙庐tra, et nous importerons des biens produits par des industries polluantes 脙聽 l芒聙聶autre bout du monde.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:53:24</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_324"/>
  </rdf:Description>
