  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_45">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_45</del:identifier>
    <del:text>They wonder when we will take responsibility. Right now, we are only excited because Trump woke us up. Basically, he just showed us that there is no such thing as a free lunch. And we are upset? The fact that we needed this wake-up call about defence is so disturbing for our citizens.
We need to remember that Europe was stronger, and can be strong again. We need to remember that still the end of the Cold War was not the end of history, that we cannot earn respect if we do not change our mindset.
We need to invest in our defence and values, and stand firm for our principles 芒聙聯 not only when it's comfortable, but also when it is not. Because to the question of whether our citizens can count on us, the answer must be 'yes'!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:41:47</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_38"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_314">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_314</del:identifier>
    <del:text>C芒聙聶est peu, car cela repose presque exclusivement sur une d脙漏marche volontaire des 脙聣tats membres. Or, si beaucoup ont d脙漏j脙聽 augment脙漏 leurs d脙漏penses de d脙漏fense, certains restent obstin脙漏ment 脙聽 la tra脙庐ne. C芒聙聶est peu, car rien ne dit que l芒聙聶on r脙漏soudra nos principales faiblesses, celles qui r脙漏sultent de la fragmentation de nos industries de d脙漏fense et celles qui sont le fruit d芒聙聶un paradoxe toxique: nos industries exportent en priorit脙漏 hors de l芒聙聶Union europ脙漏enne, et la plupart de nos 脙聣tats ach脙篓tent essentiellement hors d芒聙聶Europe. Nous ne pouvons plus nous le permettre et nous devons absolument assumer une pr脙漏f脙漏rence europ脙漏enne marqu脙漏e 芒聙聯脗聽enfin!
Le plan d芒聙聶Ursula脗聽von脗聽der脗聽Leyen arrive apr脙篓s des d脙漏cennies d芒聙聶indolence. Surtout, il ne dit pas clairement comment nous allons massivement aider l芒聙聶Ukraine; massivement, parce que notre s脙漏curit脙漏 en d脙漏pend; massivement, parce que nous sommes de plus en plus seuls 脙聽 le faire. Saluons donc le Conseil de jeudi dernier, mais soyons lucides: ce n芒聙聶est qu芒聙聶une premi脙篓re 脙漏tape. D脙漏fendre les Europ脙漏ens est une ardente obligation, qui va n脙漏cessiter des efforts et, parfois, des sacrifices. Pr脙漏server la paix en Europe est 脙聽 ce prix.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:50:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_229"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_41">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_41</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Villy S脙赂vndal</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_317">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_317</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Antonio Decaro</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_178">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_178</del:identifier>
    <del:text>There is a desperate need for progress and real equality, as the people marching on the streets all over Europe on 8脗聽March showed it very clearly, so we have to listen to those voices. As our feminist and democratic values are under attack, there is no middle ground or room for hesitation. It's either mainstreaming gender equality or mainstreaming misogyny and sexism. You have our fullest support, Commissioner, on this roadmap, and the S&amp;D Group is with you.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:23:08</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_130"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_373">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_373</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Se脙卤or脙颅as, poner a la opini脙鲁n p脙潞blica en esta encrucijada es, adem脙隆s de un intento por infantilizarla, una irresponsabilidad en un momento cr脙颅tico para nuestras democracias. El futuro de la defensa europea exigir脙隆 esfuerzo, como nuevas partidas presupuestarias, un mejor aprovechamiento de los recursos existentes y una cooperaci脙鲁n m脙隆s estrecha con nuestros socios.
Pero nadie est脙隆 hablando aqu脙颅 de eliminar la protecci脙鲁n social, las pensiones o la sanidad. Por mucho que digan S脙隆nchez y Zapatero, ni nos sobra el Ministerio de Defensa ni nos sobra el Ej脙漏rcito. La inversi脙鲁n en defensa no solo es necesaria, sino que es el mejor escudo para poder seguir disfrutando del Estado del bienestar.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:11:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_204"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_370">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_370</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Unfortunately, the turbulent developments of today芒聙聶s world show us how that expectation was wrong, and how we cannot take things for granted anymore.
Strengthening our collective defence to respond to all kinds of threats in the current circumstances is a must. The responsibility we bear to our citizens is something we cannot betray. We have to provide the right incentives to fully develop our autonomous security and build the European Defence Union.
At the same time, funding should not come at expense of our successful social and cohesion policies, which is why we need a viable investment strategy.
Finally, you cannot choose your neighbours, but you can choose your friends. This is also an opportunity for the European Union to strengthen foreign and security ties with like-minded allies and partners all over the world.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:07:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_74"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_295">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_295</del:identifier>
    <del:text>EU-kommissionens f脙露rslag 脙陇r v脙陇lkommet men, i det stora migrationspolitiska sammanhanget, otillr脙陇ckligt. Om personer utan asylsk脙陇l aldrig f脙楼tt komma till Europa hade vi aldrig beh脙露vt 脙楼terv脙陇ndande脙楼tg脙陇rder. Det 脙陇r allts脙楼 hur och var asyl s脙露ks och beviljas som beh脙露ver 脙陇ndras. D脙陇rf脙露r 脙陇r behovet av en ny 脙楼terv脙陇ndandelagstiftning 脙陇nnu ett argument f脙露r att ett nytt migrationspolitiskt system, d脙陇r asyl s脙露ks och pr脙露vas utanf脙露r Europa, beh脙露ver utformas.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:16:48</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_218"/>
  </rdf:Description>
