  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_54">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_54</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Monsieur Costa, elle ne se cache pas derri脙篓re vous, Mme von der Leyen?
Perch脙漏 la signora von der Leyen ha paura di questo Parlamento ed invoca l'articolo 122, lo stato di emergenza, per raggirare l'unica istituzione europea eletta dal popolo e per indebitare noi e i nostri figli per 850 miliardi di euro da spendere in armi.
Eppure i carri russi non sono a Varsavia, neanche a Budapest e neanche a Praga. E Parigi non brucia sotto gragnole di colpi. Quello che brucia in Francia sono le chiese cristiane. Queste sono le vere emergenze signora von der Leyen!
Sono le famiglie europee che non arrivano a fine mese e che non hanno i soldi per pagare le bollette del gas, che le politiche scellerate della sua Commissione hanno fatto lievitare esponenzialmente.
Le vere emergenze sono l'autarchia e la dittatura e la sospensione della democrazia, come 脙篓 avvenuto pochi giorni fa in Romania, che i tecnocrati di Bruxelles appoggiano e sostengono.
Le vere emergenze sono gli attentati e la criminalit脙聽 e gli atti di criminalit脙聽, che quasi giornalmente gli immigrati illegali portano a termine a spese e a danno dei cittadini europei nelle nazioni europee.
Queste sono le vere emergenze, signora von der Leyen, non la paura di vederci un soldato russo col colbacco in testa alle porte di casa. E ci venga in Parlamento, e non abbia paura, perch脙漏 qua non l'aspetta un plotone di cosacchi con le sciabole, ma i rappresentanti del popolo europeo che vogliono dire la loro sul loro futuro.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:54:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_46"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_274">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_274</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Palautusj脙陇rjestelm脙陇 on yksi iso vitsi. Euroopassa ylpeill脙陇脙陇n oikeusvaltioperiaatteesta ja sen kunnioittamisesta. Hyv脙陇 niin, mutta mik脙陇 periaate se sellainen on, joka ei mahdollista laittomasti maassa olevien palauttamista.
Palautusten tehostaminen on my脙露s turvallisuuskysymys. Erityisesti L脙陇hi-id脙陇n ja Afrikan maista tulleet muuttajat ovat selv脙陇sti yliedustettuina rikostilastoissa. Milloin Eurooppa oikein her脙陇脙陇? Kielteisen p脙陇脙陇t脙露ksen saaneet ja vakaviin rikoksiin syyllistyneet on palautettava viipym脙陇tt脙陇. Kehitysapu on teht脙陇v脙陇 ehdolliseksi sille, ett脙陇 maat suostuvat ottamaan vastaan omia kansalaisiaan. Palautuskeskuksia on sijoitettava EU-maiden ulkopuolelle.
Hyv脙陇t kollegat, tehd脙陇脙陇n t脙陇st脙陇 palautusten vuosi.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:47:56</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_132"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_395">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_395</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A Uni脙拢o Europeia reconheceu o 脙鲁bvio: a Europa n脙拢o est脙隆 pronta para se defender. A paz depende da for脙搂a, e a Europa n脙拢o tem a suficiente.脗聽Durante d脙漏cadas, acredit脙隆mos num mundo sem guerra, numa ordem baseada em regras e num continente seguro, sem investimento em defesa.
A NATO continua a ser o pilar da nossa seguran脙搂a, imaginar uma defesa europeia isolada da Alian脙搂a 脙漏 uma fantasia perigosa.
N脙拢o precisamos de um ex脙漏rcito europeu, mas de 27 for脙搂as armadas eficazes, interoper脙隆veis, com padr脙碌es comuns e capacidade de resposta coordenada. Isso significa mais harmoniza脙搂脙拢o, defesa a脙漏rea avan脙搂ada e uma ind脙潞stria de defesa robusta; assegurar o dom脙颅nio estrat脙漏gico no espa脙搂o e no ciberespa脙搂o, tudo isto s脙拢o escolhas que definir脙拢o o futuro da Europa.
Os desafios que enfrentamos n脙拢o s脙拢o te脙鲁ricos, s脙拢o reais, e a Hist脙鲁ria n脙拢o espera por quem hesita. Precisamos de uma pol脙颅tica de defesa 脙聽 altura do nosso tempo.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:39:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_210"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_225">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_225</del:identifier>
    <del:text>La escasez de medicamentos esenciales se ha convertido en un desaf脙颅o en la Uni脙鲁n Europea. Las cadenas de suministro fr脙隆giles y dependientes suponen una vulnerabilidad para nuestros sistemas de salud y nuestros pacientes. Es esencial fortalecer la innovaci脙鲁n, la producci脙鲁n y la distribuci脙鲁n dentro de la Uni脙鲁n Europea, como se est脙隆 haciendo, por ejemplo, en mi tierra, Extremadura, donde empresas como Natac est脙隆n innovando en el sector vegetal y est脙隆n ayudando en la fabricaci脙鲁n de medicamentos hu脙漏rfanos脗聽como los que tratan la ataxia de Friedreich.
La Ley de Medicamentos Esenciales es muy necesaria. Sabemos qu脙漏 hay que hacer; d脙颅ganos, se脙卤or comisario, cu脙隆ndo y c脙鲁mo, porque se necesita ya, no le quepa la menor duda.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:27:46</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_168"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_81">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_81</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:31:05</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_70"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_43">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_43</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I commend the Member States for their clear understanding that Ukraine and Europe's future requires peace through strength 芒聙聯 strength for Ukraine to stand up against Putin and against Trump. The US is forcing Ukraine into an unacceptable surrender it could also achieve without their help. If the circumstances are unfavourable for Ukraine, for Europe, we will not accept it. We have to change these circumstances towards a just peace, or accept the ugly consequences.
Now President von脗聽der脗聽Leyen said that the Parliament was right, asking for more military support all along. Translate understanding then into real united action now, and for all the Member States, President Costa 芒聙聯 some a bit more than others 芒聙聯 that means sending Ukraine the weapons it needs now. It's irritating 芒聙聯 it's appalling even 芒聙聯 that there are still warehouses where there's critical air defence that Ukraine needs now. Do what is necessary now for Ukraine, for Europe.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:38:39</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_36"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_125">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_125</del:identifier>
    <del:text>The first speaker, speaking on behalf of the Council, will be Mr Sz脜聜apka, Poland's Minister for European Union Affairs.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:08:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_173">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_173</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Pourtant, une fois de plus, la Commission europ脙漏enne d脙漏脙搂oit. Ursula脗聽von脗聽der脗聽Leyen c脙篓de face aux conservateurs. Elle nous livre une op脙漏ration de communication digne de la politique脗聽RSE d芒聙聶un grand groupe priv脙漏, o脙鹿 l芒聙聶脙漏galit脙漏 femmes-hommes est d脙漏fendue uniquement sous le prisme de b脙漏n脙漏fices 脙漏conomiques. J芒聙聶accueille donc ce texte avec lucidit脙漏. C芒聙聶est un premier pas, mais il est insuffisant.
Nous ne pourrons pas nous contenter de d脙漏clarations d芒聙聶intention. Il nous faut des engagements clairs, 脙聽 la hauteur des enjeux. 脙聙 l芒聙聶heure o脙鹿 Poutine, mais aussi tous les imp脙漏rialistes et les int脙漏gristes religieux que nous combattons, n芒聙聶attaquent pas seulement nos fronti脙篓res europ脙漏ennes, mais m脙篓nent une guerre contre les femmes, il nous faut assumer une diplomatie f脙漏ministe europ脙漏enne et leur opposer notre mod脙篓le f脙漏ministe europ脙漏en ambitieux, universaliste et combatif.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:15:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_125"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_227">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_227</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Pierre-Romain Thionnet,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_279">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_279</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Niemcy 脜聸ci脛聟gn脛聶脜聜y na siebie problem, a teraz usi脜聜uj脛聟 si脛聶 nim podzieli脛聡 z innymi narodami, co obni脜录a poziom wsp脙鲁脜聜pracy i zaufania, a tak脜录e rozbija stref脛聶 Schengen. Czas na zdecydowane dzia脜聜ania na rzecz powstrzymania imigracji. Czas na deportowanie kryminalist脙鲁w z naszego kontynentu. Czas na pe脜聜ne wdro脜录enie za脜聜o脜录e脜聞 deklaracji budapeszta脜聞skiej Patriot脙鲁w. Tylko w ten spos脙鲁b mo脜录emy uratowa脛聡 Europ脛聶.
(M脙鲁wczyni nie zgodzi脜聜a si脛聶 na pytanie zasygnalizowane przez podniesienie niebieskiej kartki przez Lukas Sieper)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:55:01</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_27"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_103">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_103</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Mathilde Androu脙芦t</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_162">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_162</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Laurence Trochu</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_189">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_189</del:identifier>
    <del:text>However, I do believe two things. First of all, without allowing men to actively, actively participate in gender equality, we will never achieve anything. So this feminist hatred against men will not bring us any further, but will polarise society instead.
Secondly, we women are part of the problem. As long as we victimise ourselves, we continue to keep the vicious circle of gender inequality intact. It's time to take responsibility for our actions and to refuse to be treated as victims. We are not victims. If we refuse to be, we are not victims.
It's time we take our rightful place in the society just because we can and not because a gender quota assigns us a spot.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:38:10</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_139"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_465">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_465</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ich kann den Grunds脙陇tzen Ihres Plans durchaus etwas abgewinnen, aber ich habe noch viele offene Fragen. Mit Sicherheit wird es wieder zu neuer Gesetzgebung kommen脗聽芒聙聯 bitte smart und ohne zus脙陇tzliche B脙录rokratie. Die Mitgliedstaaten sind aufgefordert, Steuern auf Strom zu senken und K脙露rperschaftssteuersysteme neu zu gestalten sowie Genehmigungsverfahren umzusetzen; auch sie brauchen Ihre Unterst脙录tzung.脗聽Aber auch die Ausgestaltung des Gesetzes zur Beschleunigung der industriellen Dekarbonisierung mit Resilienz- und Nachhaltigkeitskriterien sowie die Schaffung einer Wasserstoffbank l脙陇sst f脙录r mich noch einige Antworten offen, die wir mit Sicherheit in Zukunft noch diskutieren m脙录ssen.
Wichtig ist, dass unsere Unternehmen jetzt Hilfe bekommen, die im Green Deal versprochen wurde, denn unsere Betriebe ...
(Die Pr脙陇sidentin entzieht der Rednerin das Wort.)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:08:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_333"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_349">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_349</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Dubravka 脜聽uica,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_96">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_96</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Iva, huwa 脛聥arissimu li hemm b脜录onn u hemm bi脜录a' serju ta' inva脜录joni fit-territorju tal-Unjoni. Spe脛聥jalment issa bl-in脛聥ertezza li 脛隆ejjin min-na脛搂a l-o脛搂ra tal-Atlantiku. U b'hekk nifhem li l-gvernijiet Ewropej iridu jing脛搂aqdu fi sforzi kon脛隆unti fejn jid脛搂ol l-investiment personali tag脛搂hom g脛搂ad-difi脜录a. Argument li jag脛搂mel sens, per脙虏 ma nistg脛搂ux nag脛搂mlu dan askapitu tal-ambizzjonijiet u tat-tama ta脛聥-脛聥ittadini Ewropej. 脛娄bieb, fl-istess waqt u bl-istess sa脛搂脛搂a, ejja ninvestu fin-nies, fil-脛搂ajja tan-nies u mhux inaqqsuhom. Ejja 脛搂a nibba脜录aw l-ekonomija Ewropea fuq il-benesseri u mhux fuq il-gwerra, fuq il-pa脛聥i u mhux fuq il-qerda.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:48:55</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_83"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_337">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_337</del:identifier>
    <del:text>脦職脦卤脦鹿 脧聞脧聛脦炉脦卤 脦潞脦卤脦炉脧聛脦鹿脦卤 脦碌脧聛脧聣脧聞脦庐脦录脦卤脧聞脦卤:
