  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_299">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_299</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Elena Donazzan,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_107">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_107</del:identifier>
    <del:text>In December 2022, I was abducted by Russian security forces right at the border, as I was trying to reach Crimea to visit my critically ill father. My only crime was that I'm Crimean Tatar. I'm Ukrainian, born in Crimea, and I refused to take Russian passport. For Russia, that's enough to label me an enemy and throw me behind bars. During these years, I endured immense injustice and cruelty: abduction, psychological and physical abuse, interrogation, solitary confinement. Most of the time I was held in complete isolation.脗聽But you know what? I'm Crimean Tatar, and these are not the first repression in my family history.
In 1944, my grandmother was just 10 years old when she became a victim of Soviet deportation. Her entire family 芒聙聯 like hundreds of thousands of Crimean Tatars, mostly women and children, as the men were at war 芒聙聯 was declared a traitor of the motherland. They were given 20 minutes to pack. They were forced into cattle wagons and deported to Uzbekistan. Two of my grandmother's younger brothers, three-year-old Kadir-Ilyas and six-year-old Nazim, died of starvation. This is not only my family tragedy. This is the pain of every Crimean Tatar family.
Many countries have already recognised the 1944 deportation as the act of genocide against Crimean Tatar people, because history must be called by its true name. But history is repeating itself. Once again, Russia is trying to destroy us. Once again, it erases identities, rewrites borders, and crushes lives. In the occupied territories, Russia deports even ordinary civilians. They are abused, forcibly deported, subjected to forced labour. Any act of defiance, even silent, is treated as a crime. The punishment is prison.
Let me share the stories of several women I personally know. Oksana from Kherson region: before she was sent to a detention centre, she was held for six months with a bag over the head. One day she was brought to a pit and they told her, 'We will bury you alive here. No one will know where you are.' Yana from Zaporizhzhia region: she was tortured, her jaw was broken, several teeth knocked out, and then she was denied all medical care. Halyna Dovhopola from Crimea: a 70-year-old pensioner. Russian forces beat her, tortured here and tried to break her fingers. Iryna Danylovych, a Crimean journalist: she survived torture. Today she is denied medical help in prison. She has lost hearing in the ear, suffered a mini stroke, half her body is numb. She lives in constant pain with severe headaches and heart problems.
These are just a few stories. There are thousands more. Around 14脗聽000 Ukrainian civilians are currently being held in Russian prison. In prison, I constantly heard the same phrase: your Ukraine has very little time left. But I'm here, and Ukraine continues to fight, even in the face of devastating news. We are fighting for freedom, for dignity, for every human life. And we are not facing Russia alone. Russia is supported by Belarus, Iran, China and North Korea. Authoritarian regimes have united 芒聙聯 against democracy. This is more than a war for territory. This is the battle between light and darkness, between freedom and slavery, between democracy and tyranny. And Ukraine is still fighting and we are fighting for the win. But just imagine 芒聙聯 what if Ukraine falls? Who will be next?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T12:32:45</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_88"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_491">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_491</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I really beg everyone who is speaking today to keep the time, because we are already very late.
And I announce directly at the beginning that we can just take five people for the catch-the-eye procedure. So we will open it shortly and then I will close it when we have five announced, because otherwise we will be here until midnight.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:38:17</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_14"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_76">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_76</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Als EP haben wir Probleme mit der Rechtsgrundlage, und ich h脙陇tte mir auch gew脙录nscht, dass wir auch die nationale脗聽escape clause nur insoweit gelten lassen, als die zus脙陇tzlichen Ausgaben in gemeinsame R脙录stungsprojekte investiert werden, um Skaleneffekte zu erzielen, um Interoperabilit脙陇t zu erh脙露hen. Wir brauchen auch europ脙陇ische Projekte, um uns gemeinsam zu sch脙录tzen. Ein European Sky Shield w脙陇re so ein Beispiel; andere Projekte sind genannt worden.
In der Zwischenzeit sehen wir, wie die russische R脙录stungsmaschinerie auf Hochtouren l脙陇uft und schon jetzt mehr produziert, als sie in der Ukraine einsetzt. Wof脙录r wohl? Machen wir uns endlich klar: Die russische Bedrohung richtet sich gegen uns alle, und die Ukraine ist unsere erste Verteidigungslinie, die wir st脙陇rken m脙录ssen, w脙陇hrend wir das eigene Potenzial hochfahren.
Die Ukrainer sind die ersten, die Frieden wollen. Sie wollten auch den Krieg nicht. Aber sie wissen auch, wie ein russischer Frieden aussieht, ein stalinistischer Frieden im russischen Gulag. Das droht auch uns, wenn die Ukraine f脙陇llt und wir nicht verteidigungsf脙陇hig sind. Lassen wir es nicht so weit kommen! Slawa Ukrajini!
(Der Redner ist damit einverstanden, auf eine Frage nach dem Verfahren der 芒聙聻blauen Karte芒聙聹 zu antworten.)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:24:56</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_66"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_243">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_243</del:identifier>
    <del:name>脦聺脦鹿脦潞脧聦脦禄脦卤脦驴脧聜 脦聭脦陆脦卤脦麓脦鹿脧聨脧聞脦路脧聜</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_NI"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_93">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_93</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Liebe Kolleginnen und Kollegen, an diejenigen, die hier immer die alten R脙露mer zitieren, dass diejenigen, die den Frieden wollen, jetzt f脙录r den Krieg r脙录sten sollten. Ich m脙露chte euch sagen: Dann geht doch ab an die Front, aber schreit nicht nach der Bev脙露lkerung! Unsere S脙露hne, unsere Kinder kriegt ihr nicht.
Die Bev脙露lkerung in Europa sehnt sich nicht nach Krieg, sie sehnt sich nach Frieden.脗聽Und unsere Geschichte in Europa hat uns beigebracht, dass immer mehr Waffen nicht zu Frieden beitragen werden.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:44:59</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_80"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_205">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_205</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Joachim Stanis脜聜aw Brudzi脜聞ski</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_91">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_91</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Roxana M脙庐nzatu,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_203">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_203</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Atto normativo che era largamente atteso, non soltanto per ci脙虏 che 脙篓 emerso all'indomani della pandemia, quando abbiamo scoperto come Europa che la gran parte della nostra produzione avveniva al di fuori dei 27 Paesi e quindi era difficile un approvvigionamento, soprattutto in momenti di difficolt脙聽.
Oggi c'脙篓 una questione molto importante che questo atto inizia ad affrontare ed 脙篓 quella di rendere competitiva e di rendere realizzabile la produzione di medicinali, soprattutto generici, anche in Europa, mentre oggi sappiamo che la principale criticit脙聽 sta tutta qui: nel fatto che produrre il farmaco in Europa 脙篓 diventato antieconomico.
E allora 脙篓 un lavoro che inizia col Critical Medicines Act, 脙篓 un lavoro che 脙篓 stato preso dalla bussola della competitivit脙聽. Noi siamo ottimisti perch脙漏 脙篓 anche questa una questione di sovranit脙聽.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:57:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_148"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_252">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_252</del:identifier>
    <del:name>脦聲脦录脦录脦卤脦陆脦驴脧聟脦庐脦禄 脦娄脧聛脦卢脦鲁脦潞脦驴脧聜</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_ECR"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_134">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_134</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Arba Kokalari</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_338">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_338</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Times have changed: there is war in Europe, Putin threatens all of us, and this US administration leaves doubt whether they will live up to their NATO commitments. That is why I thank the Commissioner for presenting this white paper on the future of European defence, together with the earlier announcement on the programme to ReArm Europe. Let us make the best out of it 芒聙聯 let us defend our European way of life together and let us start on the front line, supporting Ukraine with whatever it takes as they defend their and our freedom. Slava Ukraini!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:27:55</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_66"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_493">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_493</del:identifier>
    <del:text>And I would again say that we closed already the catch-the-eye procedure. So for those who are now arriving, there is no chance for catch-the-eye or for blue cards.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:44:52</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_310">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_310</del:identifier>
    <del:text>A challenge for Europe in the short term is on Ukraine's battlefield. The future of Europe will be decided there. Member States should commit at least 0.25脗聽% of their GDP to military aid to Ukraine. Ukraine's defence industries should be integrated with the European one.
In the longer term, to ensure that most EU policies align with defence and security needs. Defence is the priority of priorities. We need to increase our defence spending to at least 3脗聽% of GDP in 2026 as a start. The EU was not created as a defence union. Europe flourished on US security guarantees. Everything has changed.
We will have to fill the huge security capabilities gap and diversify our security policy to build our own capabilities while trying to maintain and strengthen the transatlantic bond.
Tomorrow we will vote for a resolution on the white paper on defence. But this is just the very beginning of a difficult but very necessary journey 芒聙聯 an existential journey.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T17:42:30</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_225"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_345">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_345</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Lina G脙隆lvez</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_482">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_482</del:identifier>
    <del:text>De industri脙芦le ruggengraat van Europa, van onze familiebedrijven wordt gebogen onder bureaucratische en prijsballast. Voorzitter, technologieneutraliteit. De verbrandingsmotor verdient eerherstel. Het is tijd voor een fundamentele herziening van de Green Deal. Niet de realiteit moet zich aanpassen aan Brussel, maar Brussel moet zich aanpassen aan de gewijzigde realiteit.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:29:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_217"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_46">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_46</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Roberto Vannacci</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PfE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_272">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_272</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Toleriranje takvoga, potpuno disfunkcionalnog pa i grotesknog modela s pravom naru脜隆ava povjerenje Europljana u sustav, privla脛聧i nezakonite migracije, a tragi脛聧ni napadi mu脜隆karaca koji nisu imali pravo biti u Europi nagla脜隆avaju i te脜隆ke sigurnosne posljedice takvih trulih politika.
Bez u脛聧inkovitih povrataka, dobrovoljnih, ali i prisilnih, cijeli sustav migracija i azila gubi svaki smisao. Zato odluka o protjerivanju, odluka o neodobravanju azila mora imati konkretne posljedice ako 脜戮elimo vladavinu prava i da se Europu, njezina pravila i njezine granice nikada vi脜隆e ne shva脛聡a neozbiljno.
Uvo脛聭enje stro脜戮ih pravila, inovativnih ideja pa i deportacijskih centara izvan Europe nagradit 脛聡e pakt o migraciji i azilu koji treba uvesti i uvest 脛聡e vi脜隆e reda na europske granice. Sada njegova implementacija zato mora biti prioritet jer bez u脛聧inkovite migracijske politike koja uklju脛聧uje i u脛聧inkovitu politiku povrataka nema vjerodostojne Europe.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T16:45:06</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_202"/>
  </rdf:Description>
