  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_237">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_237</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Written Statements (Rule 178)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:45:57</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_76">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_76</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Maria Grapini</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_86">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_86</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I also believe that this House will support an even more ambitious position. It goes without saying that the transatlantic disruption caused by the new US administration has brought us long-term geopolitical changes. We must not base European security on voter attitudes in US swing states. The EU needs to plan de-risking policy towards Trump's Washington. This is not America that wants its allies to respect it. This is an America that wants its allies to fear it.
Europe must make some historical and responsible steps ahead. Bold leadership and adequate funds are needed, including through seizing EUR 200 billion of Russian assets. I always repeat that our security does not stop at our borders. That's why we have to act fast and to act now. Time is of the essence.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:36:42</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_74"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_291">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_291</del:identifier>
    <del:name>脦聯脦碌脧聨脧聛脦鲁脦鹿脦驴脧聜 脦聭脧聟脧聞脦鹿脦卢脧聜</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_348">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_348</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Rosa Serrano Sierra</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_2">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_2</del:identifier>
    <del:text>芒聙聯 European Council and Commission statements on the conclusions of the special European Council meeting of 6脗聽March脗聽2025脗聽(2025/2589(RSP));
芒聙聯 Council and Commission statements on preparation of the European Council of 20-21脗聽March脗聽2025 (2025/2544(RSP));
芒聙聯 European Council and Commission statements on European security architecture: urgent decisive steps and unwavering support for Ukraine (2025/2590(RSP)).
The President of the European Council is on his way. He was delayed by fog in Brussels, so as soon as he lands he will come straight to the Chamber. So we can go first to the Council and the Minister for the European Union, Adam Sz脜聜apka.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T09:03:14</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_334">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_334</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ten tweede, commissaris, maakt u gebruik van artikel脗聽122 van het Verdrag om het Parlement buitenspel te zetten. Van mij mag het, maar dat gaat de kwaliteit niet verbeteren. Een goed Europees defensiebeleid voer je niet in achterkamertjes.
Ten derde, commissaris, komt u volgende week met een witboek. Ik hoop dat het duidelijker en concreter is dan u vandaag bent geweest. Er moeten echt grote Europese programma芒聙聶s in staan en een routekaart voor een Europees leger. Ook dit zeg ik hier al tien jaar. U wilt de geschiedenis ingaan? Wel, commissaris, maak die routekaart voor dat Europees leger, of u mist de afspraak met de geschiedenis.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:22:28</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_78"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_341">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_341</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T18:32:02</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_232">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_232</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ce n芒聙聶est pas tellement la faute des Indiens ou des Chinois, non: c芒聙聶est la faute des Europ脙漏ens. Pourquoi? Parce que nous sommes d脙漏pendants en premier lieu des choix que font les grandes multinationales pharmaceutiques. Ce sont elles qui d脙漏cident quoi produire, o脙鹿 produire, combien produire et 脙聽 quel prix vendre,脗聽m脙陋me lorsqu芒聙聶elles ont re脙搂u des subventions publiques 脙聽 la recherche ou 脙聽 la production.
Ce qu芒聙聶il faut casser aujourd芒聙聶hui, c芒聙聶est le monopole qu芒聙聶ont ces entreprises, et pour ce faire les ONG, les associations et m脙陋me les syndicats nous ont d脙漏j脙聽 donn脙漏 la marche 脙聽 suivre: il s芒聙聶agit de cr脙漏er une infrastructure publique pour la recherche et le d脙漏veloppement en Europe. C芒聙聶est possible. Vous trouvez 800脗聽milliards pour les armes; vous allez bien trouver quelques milliards pour la sant脙漏. Qu芒聙聶est-ce que vous attendez?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:36:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_22"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_259">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_259</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Benedetta Scuderi</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_Verts_ALE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_208">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_208</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Wir brauchen mehr Produktionskapazit脙陇ten in der Europ脙陇ischen Union. Wir brauchen eine ausfallsichere Lieferkette, das hei脙聼t, nicht nur ein Hersteller darf ein Produkt liefern. Und wir m脙录ssen die Abh脙陇ngigkeit von Drittstaaten drastisch reduzieren. Daf脙录r brauchen wir gezielte Investitionen, wir brauchen strategische Unabh脙陇ngigkeit. Es ist gut, dass die Kommission die MEAT-Kriterien endlich wahrnimmt und ernst nimmt und damit nicht nur den Preis als entscheidendes Kriterium hat. Als Sozialdemokratinnen und Sozialdemokraten haben wir das schon lange gefordert, aber die Wahrheit ist auch: Wir werden daf脙录r Geld brauchen, und daran m脙录ssen wir jetzt gemeinsam arbeiten.
(Der Redner ist damit einverstanden, auf eine Frage nach dem Verfahren der 芒聙聻blauen Karte芒聙聹 zu antworten.)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:04:55</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_153"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_108">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_108</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I now pass the floor to Ukrainian frontline medical volunteer and humanitarian activist Tata Kepler.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T12:39:50</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_408">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_408</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ei sunt con脠聶tien脠聸i c脛聝 f脛聝r脛聝 ajutorul SUA, ap脛聝rarea Uniunii Europene ar sc脛聝dea semnificativ. Dar mai sunt con脠聶tien脠聸i c脛聝 siguran脠聸a depinde de c脙垄t de mult investe脠聶ti 脙庐n ea. Dou脛聝 aspecte trebuie avute 脙庐n vedere de Comisie 脠聶i Consiliul European atunci c脙垄nd vor stabili regulile concrete ale achizi脠聸iilor: transparen脠聸a 脠聶i obiectivitatea.

脙聨n privin脠聸a obiectivit脛聝脠聸ii, s脛聝 nu uit脛聝m ceva: Vestul n-a trecut prin 50 de ani de comunism, unde nu a existat pia脠聸脛聝, competen脠聸脛聝, investi脠聸ii 脙庐n bun脛聝starea general脛聝, transparen脠聸脛聝, ci doar lozinci sovietice bine ambalate.

Decalajul este at脙垄t de mare 脙庐nc脙垄t, a trata egal necesarul de investi脠聸ii 脙庐n ap脛聝rare ar fi o nedreptate.

Ar fi o neglijare a aspira脠聸iilor cet脛聝脠聸enilor din Rom脙垄nia, Bulgaria 脠聶i restul 脠聸脛聝rilor din fostul bloc comunist 脙庐n a-脠聶i ob脠聸ine infrastructuri civilizate 脙庐n materie de s脛聝n脛聝tate, educa脠聸ie, transport, administra脠聸ie.
脠聵i asta deoarece dac脛聝 aloci bani pentru ap脛聝rare, trebuie s脛聝 脙庐i iei din alt脛聝 parte!

Foarte mul脠聸i ani, 脙庐n timp ce 脠聸脛聝rile socialiste erau la frontiera Europei, orientate for脠聸at, cu glon脠聸ul la t脙垄mpl脛聝, c脛聝tre ru脠聶i, Vestul s-a dezvoltat.

Rom脙垄nii au ap脛聝rat Europa nu o dat脛聝 脠聶i n-au vrut niciodat脛聝 s脛聝 o cucereasc脛聝.
Acum este r脙垄ndul Europei!</del:text>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_292"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_337">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_337</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Jon脙隆s Fern脙隆ndez</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_440">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_440</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Es ist schon gesagt worden, die Klimaziele erreichen wir nur mit einer wettbewerbsf脙陇higen Wirtschaft. Aber zur Wahrheit geh脙露rt halt, dass die Arbeitspl脙陇tze, die in dieser Wirtschaft geschaffen werden, langfristig nur dann da sind, wenn die Wirtschaft wettbewerbsf脙陇hig ist. Wettbewerbsf脙陇higkeit erreicht man nicht durch mehr Subventionen oder durch zus脙陇tzliche Regulierung, sondern Wettbewerbsf脙陇higkeit erreicht man dadurch, dass man Direktinvestitionen nach Europa holt, Wettbewerbsf脙陇higkeit erreicht man dadurch, dass europ脙陇ische Firmen innovative Produkte herstellen und dass die Abgabenlast gesenkt wird.
Ich w脙录rde mich freuen, wenn wir einen viel, viel st脙陇rkeren Fokus auf diesen Punkt setzen: Wie k脙露nnen wir die Kosten runter kriegen? Wie k脙露nnen wir die Unternehmen langfristig wettbewerbsf脙陇hig kriegen, und nicht: Wie schaffen wir neue Regulierungen und neue Subventionen?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:35:29</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_196"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_295">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_295</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Victor Negrescu</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_S&amp;D"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_23">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_23</del:identifier>
    <del:text></del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T10:12:13</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_20"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/role_participant_1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Role"/>
    <del:name>President</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_544">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_544</del:identifier>
    <del:text>C芒聙聶est l脙聽, la caract脙漏ristique de cette Union europ脙漏enne, aujourd芒聙聶hui: un m脙漏pris pour la vie des Palestiniens! Parce que oui, vous avez r脙漏ussi 脙聽 faire un discours en disant: 脗芦Ah! La situation 脙聽 Gaza empire芒聙娄脗禄, sans mentionner pourquoi elle empire. Pourquoi est-ce qu芒聙聶elle empire? Eh bien, parce qu芒聙聶Isra脙芦l bloque toute aide humanitaire, toute nourriture, et m脙陋me l芒聙聶脙漏lectricit脙漏. Qu芒聙聶est-ce que cela veut dire? Sans 脙漏lectricit脙漏, pas de d脙漏salinisation de l芒聙聶eau, et donc pas d芒聙聶eau potable. Ainsi, les gens, les familles, les enfants n芒聙聶ont pas d芒聙聶eau potable, et vous, vous 脙陋tes l脙聽 en train de rigoler! Comment est-ce possible, Monsieur le Ministre? Comment est-ce possible, s芒聙聶il vous pla脙庐t?
Alors, aujourd芒聙聶hui, cette complicit脙漏 europ脙漏enne et ce manque de respect pour la vie des Palestiniens doivent cesser, parce que cela va se payer cash! Je vous le promets!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T23:06:49</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_22"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_533">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_533</del:identifier>
    <del:text>'Attacks against civilian infrastructure, especially electricity, are war crimes': those are not my words, those are the words of the President of the Commission, Ursula von der Leyen, who rightfully called out Russia but refuses to call out Israel when they deprive Palestinians of water, food and electricity. War crimes are war crimes, and international law applies to everyone. The obvious double standards that we are seeing are undermining the EU's credibility across the world and even with its own citizens.
The provisional measures ordered by the International Court of Justice in weighing the allegation of genocide brought against Israel specifically referred to the facilitation of aid deliveries. In the International Criminal Court, one of the charges against Netanyahu is that he is using starvation as a method of warfare.
We had the Association Council meeting in February, and some of us naively thought that maybe some strong words would be said to the Israeli authorities; maybe they would be asked to uphold international law. But instead, what we have seen is that things have gotten worse since that meeting. Israel is escalating its violation of international law.
So the question is: when is the EU going to finally stand up for international law and human rights?</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:50:55</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_371"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_78">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_78</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Die Ukraine braucht Sicherheitsgarantien, die den Namen auch verdienen, und der britische Premierminister hat gesagt 芒聙聻boots on the ground and planes in the air芒聙聹. Ich glaube, das w脙陇re nach Ende des Kriegszustandes eine gemeinsame Antwort auf die russische Bedrohung.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:27:33</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_66"/>
