  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_91">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_91</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ik heb de heren Merz en Macron gehoord. Frankrijk en Duitsland doen mee en als zij meedoen, dan zullen andere landen sowieso mee instappen. Doe dit gewoon. Neem ook de Noren en de Britten mee aan tafel. We weten allemaal waarom. Laat ons niet gewoon meer van hetzelfde doen, alleen maar een "coalition of the willing" vormen. Er is nog 脙漏脙漏n grote stap die u samen met de Commissie moet zetten 芒聙聯 en ik heb dit vandaag maar een paar keer gehoord 芒聙聯脗聽nl. de stap naar een Europees leger. Dat is wat we nodig hebben.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:42:34</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_78"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_453">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_453</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Algunos est脙隆n promocionando aqu脙颅 la vuelta a los combustibles f脙鲁siles, al gas, que fue verdaderamente el problema que lastr脙鲁 nuestra competitividad en los 脙潞ltimos a脙卤os aumentando los precios de la energ脙颅a. Por eso, cuando estos grupos hablan de promover de nuevo los f脙鲁siles, realmente quienes se frotan las manos son Putin y Trump. Por lo tanto, nosotros debemos continuar apostando por una energ脙颅a limpia 芒聙聰preferiblemente renovable芒聙聰 y apostar por las interconexiones. Adem脙隆s, la financiaci脙鲁n es una condici脙鲁n imprescindible para lograrlo. Damos la bienvenida a los 100脗聽000 millones de euros, pero creemos que esto debe continuar en el nuevo marco financiero plurianual.
Miren, vivimos en un mundo hostil, pero no debemos hacer caso a la propaganda antieuropea. Valoremos nuestra posici脙鲁n favorable y lo que hemos construido. Nuestras condiciones de vida tambi脙漏n forman parte de nuestra competitividad.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T20:51:54</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_160"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_379">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_379</del:identifier>
    <del:text>O Livro Branco sobre o futuro da defesa europeia 脙漏 um bom 芒聙聰 脙漏 um excelente 芒聙聰 alicerce, sobre o qual construiremos uma verdadeira Uni脙拢o Europeia da Defesa.脗聽As nossas prioridades s脙拢o claras: uma abordagem abrangente 脙聽 seguran脙搂a europeia, aumentar significativamente o investimento em defesa e desenvolver uma ind脙潞stria de defesa cred脙颅vel, aut脙鲁noma e soberana.
A Comiss脙拢o apresentou o plano ReArm Europe para mobilizar, inicialmente, 800 mil milh脙碌es de euros. Apoiamos estas medidas, mas exigimos compromissos vinculativos e imediatos com responsabilidades atribu脙颅das a todos os Estados芒聙聭Membros.
A diplomacia sem capacidade de dissuas脙拢o 脙漏 um pleno exerc脙颅cio de fraqueza. 脙聣 tempo de honrar a responsabilidade hist脙鲁rica que nos foi confiada, e a Hist脙鲁ria ser脙隆 escrita em fun脙搂脙拢o da nossa a脙搂脙拢o ou da nossa ina脙搂脙拢o.
(O orador aceita responder a uma pergunta 脗芦cart脙拢o azul脗禄)</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:20:35</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_82"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_481">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_481</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Ten tweede is er een ander probleem van het industriebeleid. Dat is dat we de laatste jaren heel veel publiek geld, belastinggeld, hebben gegeven aan bedrijven die dat in hun eigen zakken hebben gestoken, aan de aandeelhouders hebben gegeven zonder banen te garanderen in Europa. Ook op dat vlak schiet de Commissie tekort. Welke garanties zijn er voor de arbeiders, voor de werknemers?
Ten derde wilt u nu ook nog eens de sociale en ecologische verantwoordelijkheid van multinationals afzwakken wat betreft ruwe grondstoffen. Dat wil zeggen dat we meer plunderingen zullen zien in Oost-Congo, dat we Rwanda nog meer zullen aanmoedigen om daar de oorlog op te stoken. Dat is niet de oplossing. Wij hebben een publiek industriebeleid nodig.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T21:28:16</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_22"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_79">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_79</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Les grandes temp脙陋tes exigent de rompre avec l芒聙聶habitude, et le moment est venu pour nous aussi de nous d脙漏faire de nos meubles. La Russie nous menace directement, et les 脙聣tats-Unis nous abandonnent l脙垄chement. Eh bien, c芒聙聶est le moment de v脙漏rit脙漏 de l芒聙聶Europe.
Il nous revient d脙漏sormais, 脙聽 nous et 脙聽 nous seuls, d芒聙聶aider massivement notre premi脙篓re ligne de d脙漏fense qu芒聙聶est la r脙漏sistance ukrainienne. Le Conseil europ脙漏en l芒聙聶affirme, mais cela suppose de prendre des d脙漏cisions fortes, devant lesquelles nos 脙聣tats reculent encore, comme la saisie des 209脗聽milliards d芒聙聶avoirs publics russes gel脙漏s en Europe et leur affectation 脙聽 l芒聙聶Ukraine.
Il nous revient aussi d脙漏sormais, 脙聽 nous et 脙聽 nous seuls, d芒聙聶assurer notre propre s脙漏curit脙漏 et de construire une d脙漏fense autonome. Nos dirigeants l芒聙聶affirment, mais cela suppose d芒聙聶aller plus loin que ce qui fut annonc脙漏 jeudi. Lan脙搂ons un emprunt commun finan脙搂ant des programmes europ脙漏ens et assurons-nous que cet argent serve 脙聽 d脙漏velopper les industries europ脙漏ennes 芒聙聯脗聽et pas 脙聽 empiler les F-35.
Nous avons besoin d芒聙聶agir plus, et plus en Europ脙漏ens. 脨隆脨禄脨掳脨虏脨掳 脨拢脨潞脩聙脨掳脩聴脨陆脩聳 (脗芦Slava Oukra脙炉ni脗禄)! Vive l芒聙聶Europe libre!</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T11:28:22</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_68"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_161">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_161</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Me脛聭utim, 脜戮elim vas podsjetiti da za svaki euro koji zaradi mu脜隆karac, 脜戮ena zaradi 0,87 eura. Trenutno stanje u Europskom parlamentu, 脜戮ena ima oko 40 posto, ali me脛聭u liderima politi脛聧kih grupacija i pojedinaca, predsjednicima vlada ta brojka puno je manja.
Naravno da prepreke poput rodnog jaza u pla脛聡ama, staklenog stropa i napla脛聡enog ku脛聡anskog rada i dalje ograni脛聧avaju 脜戮ene. Klju脛聧ne su nam politike koje podr脜戮avaju pristup kvalitetnom obrazovanju, poduzetni脜隆tvu i financijskim resursima i naravno bolja ravnote脜戮a izme脛聭u privatnog i poslovnog 脜戮ivota, pa i u ruralnim podru脛聧jima, nemojmo na to zaboraviti.
Me脛聭utim, vi脜隆e od polovice svjetske populacije 脛聧inimo mi, 脜戮ene. U Europskoj uniji ima nas 52 posto. Imamo potencijala preoblikovati sustave mo脛聡i, ekonomiju i dru脜隆tvene vrijednosti. Ali ne kao ra脜隆timani orkestar, ne kao ideologija, ve脛聡 kao one koje doista 脜戮ele politiku iskoristiti u svrhu pobolj脜隆anja uvjeta 脜戮ena i da svim 脜戮enama u Europskoj uniji bude bolje.
Ne脛聡emo to posti脛聡i ako 脛聡emo se samo nadmetati u tome tko je u pravu, a tko nije.
Zaklju脛聧it 脛聡u, ekonomska neovisnost omogu脛聡uje jedino slobodu izbora i na tome trebamo raditi.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T13:59:53</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_115"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_202">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_202</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Therefore, we welcome the ambition to maintain a list of critical medicines for which European research and production capacities would be granted. But it is not an easy task. As critical, we consider a wide range of medicines, including those old simple molecules whose production was, due to cost optimisation, transferred outside the EU in the past decades. And now we want them back.
Also, we shall consider what should be the role of the EU here. In my opinion, mainly coordination of fair distribution of supportive projects among Member States to avoid duplication and at the end, after implementation, coordination of logistics of critical medicines.
However, we believe that tools like CMA and Pharma Package can contribute positively to increase medicine supplies resilience on our continent, and in this regard, Mr Commissioner, you have our full support.
However, I would like to extend that attracting private investments of pharma industry in the EU would require at the same time, in parallel, energy cost reductions, decreasing of obligations linked to the medicines lifecycle and also less bureaucracy, which is exactly the opposite of which some of your colleagues, Mr Commissioner, are doing.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T14:55:45</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_147"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_528">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_528</del:identifier>
    <del:text>I have seen it with my own eyes when I visited Rafah in Egypt three weeks ago, how children being mutilated and how the Israeli right-wing government refused to let basic humanitarian aid enter. And don't forget the Israeli annexation of the West Bank that is taking place right now.
Colleagues, Netanyahu is prolonging the conflict, refusing to move to the next phase of the ceasefire. To all colleagues still defending the Israeli far-right government, what more do you want Netanyahu to do before enough is enough? Take off your political blinders.
Wasn't it some of you who said all lives matters when we were discussing racism in EU? So what about the Palestinians' lives? Aren't they a part of all of us? International law is not cherry picking.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T22:43:44</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_366"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_97">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_97</del:identifier>
    <del:name>M脙漏lissa Camara,</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_250">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_250</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Micha脜聜 Szczerba</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
