    <del:name>Sun脛聧ana Glavak</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_382">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_382</del:identifier>
    <del:text>Komission puolustuksen valkoinen kirja on vasta alku tarpeellisille johtop脙陇脙陇t脙露ksille. Puolustusalan yhteisty脙露ss脙陇 on ment脙陇v脙陇 paljon pidemm脙陇lle kuin mit脙陇 komissio nyt esitt脙陇脙陇.
Kun laitamme lis脙陇脙陇 rahaa puolustukseen, meid脙陇n on varmistettava, ett脙陇 n脙陇m脙陇 rahat tuovat turvaa my脙露s taloudellisesti. Eurooppalainen puolustusteollisuus tarvitsee pitk脙陇lle tulevaisuuteen vakaita hankintaohjelmia. EU-rahalla tulee luoda osaamista ja ty脙露paikkoja Eurooppaan 芒聙聯 ei valtamerten ylitse. Buy European.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T19:23:37</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_273"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem20">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"/>
    <del:identifier>creitem20</del:identifier>
    <del:name>White paper on the future of European defence (debate)</del:name>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_355">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"/>
    <del:identifier>participant_355</del:identifier>
    <del:name>Laurent Castillo</del:name>
    <del:isAffiliatedWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/org_PPE"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_241">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"/>
    <del:identifier>contribution_241</del:identifier>
    <del:text>But one major thing still remains and that is returns. Too many people without the right to stay in Europe are still in Europe. I would say it's quite hard to actually find Member States across Europe that are effective in their work that a no actually means a no. So, as the EPP, we have been calling for this proposal and we welcome it because we cannot have a system where people that are denied asylum can simply move to another Member State to avoid being returned. There must be clear rules, firm obligation and real consequences for non-compliance.
I think this proposal in general creates now the common framework that we need. It closes many of the loopholes and it puts forward also a legal framework for return hubs. These are key messages that ensure that the people that do not have the right to stay in Europe also must leave Europe.
But this is only a starting point. Negotiations must make this proposal as strong and effective as possible. Our system demands results and I think that those days of wishful thinking are over. Now we need a policy that is in contact with reality and from EPP we are ready to deliver and we are ready to get to work.</del:text>
    <del:timestamp rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-03-11T15:58:14</del:timestamp>
    <del:madeBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_176"/>
  </rdf:Description>
